title: orange salad
directions: Blend jello, Cool Whip, sour cream and coconut in large bowl. Add oranges, pineapple and pecans to Cool Whip mixture.
Fold gently until all ingredients are blended.
Chill.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: strawberries-in-the-snow
directions: In large bowl, mix hot water and jello. Blend in strawberries and juice. Pour 2/3 of the mixture into a mold. Cover and refrigerate about 30 minutes or until nearly set. Add marshmallows to remaining 1/3 mixture. Stir and refrigerate for same amount of time. When set, add Cool Whip to jello and marshmallow mixture. Pour on top of jello in mold. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add yolks and mix well.
Gradually add milk and stir until smooth.
Add butter.
Cook and stir over high heat until thickened (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in flavorings.
Cover and beat whites.
Add sugar gradually.
Spread over cooked filling, which has been poured into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: brownies
directions: Mix with a spoon.
Put half in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of caramels and a large package of chocolate chips.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and sugar. Stir in egg and flour. Gradually add milk, beating well. Pour into graham cracker crust (9-inch). Bake 35 minutes at 350°. If desired, top with cherry or pineapple pie filling.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: texas stew
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet, brown but not crisp.
Add next 6 ingredients and simmer a short time.
Add bouillon cubes with hot water and cook 1 hour.
Add potatoes and cook 1/2 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 sections.
Mix some cinnamon and sugar in bowl.
Use lots of cinnamon.
Put biscuits in bowl and coat well.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Throw biscuits in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done.
Use temperature on biscuit cans.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
together and roll into little balls the size of a buckeye.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Melt in double liner the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip the buckeye balls by a toothpick into the melted chocolate and paraffin.
Leave a small place on the top of the balls to look like a buckeye.
Makes 12 dozen balls.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and cut up chicken breasts.
Mix soup, broth, salt and pepper.
Mix well with chopped chicken and pour into baking dish. In separate boiler, melt butter; add flour and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown, about 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine both types of corn with eggs.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, seasoned salt, onion and dry mustard.
Add to corn mixture.
Stir in milk and butter.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburg, onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: maple rosemary glazed chicken legs
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, heat the vegetable stock over medium heat.
Add the onions, carrot, jalapeno peppers, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Braise, covered, for 5 to 7 minutes or until the onions and carrots are soft.
Add the tomatoes with their juice and the sugar; cook for 5 minutes over high heat.
Stir in the beans and bulgur and reduce heat to low. Simmer the chili, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until thickened.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes quickly down through the cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Make holes 1 inch apart.
After poking holes, combine pudding mix with sugar in bowl.
Gradually add milk.
Beat at low speed for not more than 1 minute.
Quickly, before pudding thickens, pour about 1/2 of the thin pudding evenly over warm cake and into the holes to make stripes.
Allow remaining pudding to thicken slightly, then spoon over top.
Chill at least 1 hour. May top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake about 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with mixed fruit if desired.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, pineapple juice and vinegar. Cook until thickened.
Combine with equal parts of Cool Whip.

title: monkey bread
directions: Late in the evening, place rolls in Bundt pan. Pour melted (not warm) butter over top.
Sprinkle with sugar, pudding, cinnamon and nuts.
Cover with towel and allow to stand overnight to raise.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Invert pan on plate to serve.
Very good for breakfast.

title: aunt viola's donut holes
directions: Mix in mixer.
Drop by small spoon's full in deep hot oil. May shake in bag of sugar or powdered sugar.
Mixture keeps well in refrigerator.

title: swedish cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together thoroughly.
Combine enough coarse bread crumbs to be absorbed by 1 cup milk.
Mix all together.
Mixture should be rather moist.
Add a little milk, if necessary.
Make into small balls and place on large baking sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
To serve, place in chafing dish.
Add 1 can beef consomme soup.
Yield:
about 100 meat balls.

title: cheesecake
directions: Pack into 9-inch pie pan.

title: meat-za-pie
directions: Combine meat, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Pat mixture, with a fork, firmly and evenly over bottom and sides of plate.
Spread tomato paste over meat mixture.
Add mushrooms.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Slowly boil white sugar, brown sugar and milk until mixture makes a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, Marshmallow Fluff and peanut butter. Stir until creamy and pour in greased pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, then combine all ingredients. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: apple baked squash
directions: Mix the brown sugar, margarine, flour, salt and cinnamon together until well mixed and set aside.
Peel and slice the squash and apples into thin (1/8 inch or less) slices.
Alternate layers of squash, then apples in a 1 1/2-quart covered baking dish until half of the squash and apples are used.
Spread less than half of the brown sugar mixture on top of the squash-apple layers. Continue to alternate the squash and apples until each is used up.
Top with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Cover and cook in microwave on High for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes, or bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecued pork sandwiches
directions: Cut pork across the grain into very thin slices; set aside.

title: sunday gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken in oil. Remove with slotted spoon and keep warm. In drippings, saute onion and celery until tender. Stir in seasonings, broth, rice and chicken; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in tomatoes, shrimp and okra. Cook 10 minutes or until the shrimp turn pink, stirring occasionally.

title: mom's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in the shortening; mix well. Add buttermilk and yeast; work until flour mixture is moist. Flour counter top; roll out dough.
Spread butter, sugar and cinnamon to your liking.
Roll into jelly roll; cut.
Place rolls in pan; let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until brown. Mix powdered sugar and milk to make glaze; pour over hot rolls.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each buttermilk biscuit in 4 pieces. Put 2 tubes of biscuits in greased Bundt pan.

title: toll house pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; add flour and sugar. Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted room temperature butter; stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.
This recipe will serve 7 people.

title: white punch
directions: Make an ice ring with 1 quart of the white grape juice, diluted with 1 cup water, and the grapes.
Freeze the day before. Chill the remaining beverages.
When well chilled, pour over the ice ring, in a punch bowl, and serve.

title: chicken pasta primavera
directions: Cook broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot, in oil, about 10 minutes in skillet, on medium heat, stirring frequently, until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Stir in chicken, salt and tomatoes. Heat about 3 minutes, until chicken is hot.
Spoon chicken mixture over macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: candied fruit cake
directions: Cut up	fruit
and
nuts.
Sift
together flour, baking powder and salt.
Dredge
fruit and nuts in flour.
Beat eggs; add sugar. Pour over dredged fruit and nuts.	Mix well.
Bake in paper-lined pans at
275° on bottom rack of oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. (Use
loaf	pans.)	Or
you may use a 10-inch tube pan and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: white chip orange cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in egg and orange peel.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add all ingredients into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: red apple salad
directions: Combine sugar, salt, candies and 3 cups water in a saucepan. Heat, stirring until candies are dissolved.
Add apples; cover. Cook slowly until
just tender, turning occasionally to color evenly.
Drain and chill.
Mix cheese with green pepper; stuff apples.
Serve on watercress or lettuce.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: shrimp stuffed peppers
directions: Remove stem end and seeds from green peppers. Dip in boiling water; let stand for a few minutes and drain. In a mixing bowl, combine rice, shrimp, tomato puree, horseradish, hot pepper sauce and lemon juice. Mix well.
Season to taste. Stuff peppers with mixture and bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated and peppers are tender. Makes 1 serving.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and margarine, in the blender.
Heat cheese and margarine.
Put on top of peas in chafing dish.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until cranberries begin to pop.
Add marshmallows, cut in quarters; then mix jello and boiling water.
When jello is dissolved, add apples, drained pineapple and pecans.
Stir and mix with cranberry mixture.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the Doritos and chill.
Add the Doritos before serving.

title: oatmeal cinnamon crispies
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar gradually, then molasses and beat until the mixture is light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time. Shut off mixer and add the baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla. Blend. Gradually add flour and blend. Stir in oats and nuts. On greased cookie sheets, drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake for 5 to 9 minutes in 375° oven until medium brown and crinkly looking. Makes roughly 24 dozen cookies. They freeze well. Great recipe for a cookie exchange because it makes so many.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well by hand.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Unfold 1 pie crust and place in bottom of a Pyrex pie dish. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Unfold second pie crust and place on top.
Crimp the edges together tightly. Bake 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken in a garden
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of dish.
Combine everything except onions.
Stir in 1/2 cup of onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes and then put the rest of the onions on top and bake 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cranberries; save the juice.
Mix jello with 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1 cup pineapple and cranberry juice.
Mix together and stir in cranberries, pineapple and pecans.
Chill.

title: 1-2-3 bread pudding
directions: Butter toast generously.
Scald milk; add beaten eggs and sugar to scalded milk; pour milk over toast.
Bake in greased pan at 350° until done, about 1/2 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all together (use hands).
Drop on cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly. Bake at 350° until slightly brown. (If cookies are too flat, add more oatmeal).
Makes about 150 cookies.

title: lil's jello salad
directions: Use an 11 x 13-inch square glass dish or Tupperware dish.

title: mulled cider
directions: Bring 2-quarts water to boil and add tea bags to steep.
Add sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon hearts, sticks and cloves.
Add cider and simmer for 2 hours.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: easy potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix potatoes, sour cream, cheese, soup and onion.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Toss crumbs with margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except berries.
Then beat until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: ham salad(farm journal cookbook, circa 1959)
directions: Put ham, celery and pickle through a coarse blade of food chopper. Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Spread on rolls. Makes 4 cups; enough to cover about 40 rolls.

title: mcdonald's biscuits
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening and mix until crumbly.
Make a paste of yeast and warm water and add to ingredients.
Add buttermilk; mix well.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples in a large bowl.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a small bowl.
Sprinkle over apples and toss gently to mix.
Let stand until a little juice forms, approximately 10 minutes.

title: the ryan whoopie pie
directions: Cookie Ingredients:

Blend eggs, sugar and shortening, then add cocoa, tartar and soda. Next add salt and vanilla. Blend well. Add 2 cups flour and 1 cup milk. Mix. Add remaining flour and milk; mix. Drop by teaspoon to greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Do not remove skin from chicken.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until brown and tender.
Remove from pan and place in a dish with a cover.
Pour sauce over wings, shake to cover.
Serve.

title: cottage pudding(actually a cake)
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Add sugar, egg, shortening and milk. Mix to a stiff batter. Bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until center springs back when pressed or straw comes out clean. Serve with chocolate or lemon sauce.

title: ham delight
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, sesame seed, grated onion and Worcestershire sauce together.
Spread onto rolls, then add ham and cheese together; place on rolls.
Heat for about 15 minutes at 350°.
This can be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and refrigerate.

title: jewish chopped liver(american pate)
directions: Peel onions and carrots. Cut onions in fourths and slice. Slice carrots. Saute in enough oil to almost cover. Remove onions and carrots. Save oil.
Broil liver and cut in 1-inch cubes when done.
May be seasoned.

Put everything through grinder or food processor. Add enough oil to moisten. Salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate before serving. Can be served on crackers or as an appetizer on bed of lettuce with a cherry tomato.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and press
seams together in 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan.
Make a small lip with the rolls around the sides of the pan.
Bake until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter, peanut butter and walnuts, if you like.
Beat until glossy.
Turn into a buttered dish.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Cut and enjoy.

title: zucchini coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and oil; add pineapple and shredded zucchini.
Stir in dry ingredients until moistened.
Turn into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: potato-cucumber soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until tender; drain.
Stir in cucumber, pepper, cream, milk and onion.
Simmer until cucumber is tender.
Add dill.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in large skillet and drain off fat.
Place all the ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours (on high 3 hours).
Ingredients may be increased by half for a 5-quart model.

title: cowboy baked beans
directions: Mix together and put in crock-pot. Cook on low for 8 hours. Can use this as dip also.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening (I prefer Crisco); add sugar.
Stir and let cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients and water, then nuts and bits.
Pour in greased 16 x 10-inch pan; spread evenly and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Cut in bars or squares when cool.
Makes delicious dessert if cut a little larger, topped with ice cream and chocolate sauce.
Very popular.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up until thick and clear.
Add Jell-O.
Wash, cap and drain strawberries.
Put into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Pour the cooked mixture over the strawberries. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: dreamy fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, orange segments, marshmallows and coconut together.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill several hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve on salad greens.

title: cajun rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a large saucepan.
Drain fat.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and picante sauce.
Simmer until rice is tender and water is cooked out.
Transfer to large casserole dish.
Pour 3 tablespoons of picante sauce over mixture.
Spread Cheddar cheese over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Beat all ingredients to mix thoroughly.
Place in 1-quart glass jar.
Cover loosely.
Set in warm place for 3 to 4 days.
Will rise and become smelly, it's still alright.
Then keep in refrigerator until used.
As it is used, replenish by adding 1 teaspoon sugar, 1/2 cup of water and 1 cup of flour.
Leave in warm place to rework.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1/4-inch strips. Sprinkle with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
In a large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook until tender.
Blend cornstarch, Worcestershire and water.
Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring until clear and thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Serve over bed of rice.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in this order:
Oil, sugar, eggs (beaten until fluffy), honey, water, flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, nuts and raisins.
Mix in fruit and nuts by hand. Put batter in small greased bread pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon together.
Press half of mixture into a 9-inch greased square pan. Cover with diced uncooked rhubarb.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook until thick and clear, then pour over top of rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and celery; saute.
Stir in flour.
Add catsup, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and chili powder; stir.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased pan with crushed crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients and place on crushed crackers, topping with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter carob brownies
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jug and complete filling with water.

title: cream of oyster soup
directions: Blend flour into melted butter; add milk.
Cook until thick; add seasoning.
Add oysters and liquor.
Cook until oysters curl.

title: peaches 'n cream crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange peaches in an 8-inch baking dish.
Combine oats, brown sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream. Serves 6.

title: boiled dinner (or one pot dinner)
directions: In a large pot, put green beans in with just enough water to cover beans.
Place sliced ham on top of beans.
Place potatoes on top of ham.
Cut cabbage in quarters and place on top of ham, then place corn on top of cabbage.
Put top on pot and cook until potatoes are tender.
Do not stir.
When done, take food out in layers and place in bowls.
Cook about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Put in the flavoring.
Mix flour, sugar and salt. Rub into butter.
Knead to a paste.
Form into a thick roll and put into refrigerator overnight.
Cut 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken and soup.
Boil noodles 1/2 done and add to mixture.
Mix in broccoli.
Top with Velveeta cheese and let melt while baking.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dipping sauce(for onion rings, fried mushrooms or hard pretzels)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Spread Cheez Whiz in casserole dish and pour rest of ingredients into dish.
Cover top with some cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: Beat.
Mixture will be runny.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 18 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix mayonnaise, vinegar, garlic, basil, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper. Stir in pasta, cherry tomatoes, green pepper, onion, olives and cheese.
Place in refrigerator and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Divide all ingredients, except tomatoes and sauce, in half. Layer in well-greased 3-quart casserole.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Disregard instructions on box of cake mix.
Mix cake mix, margarine or oil and eggs until blended.
You may add chocolate chips, M&M's, raisins, nuts or any other add-ins.
You may also frost the cookies.
Bake at 325° until edges are light brown.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; add coconut and pecans.
Brown lightly and set aside.
In a mixer, combine cream cheese and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 of this mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 jar caramel sauce on each, then sprinkle 1/4 coconut-pecan mixture on each pie.
Repeat layers. Freeze well.
Serve right from the freezer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, eggs and milk in a medium bowl. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread croutons on the bottom, then spread drained sausage on top.
Add mixture from bowl on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemon fluff(great lite dessert)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Scrape rind of one lemon into Jell-O.
Put in refrigerator until just starting to jell. Remove.
Sprinkle 4 or 5 crushed graham crackers in oblong container.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch glass dish; pour in cherry filling.
Pour dry cake mix over cherry filling.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake until brown in 350° oven.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of potatoes into baking dish.
Combine flour and salt; sprinkle half over potatoes.
Repeat.
Pour milk over and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in microwave oven for 20 minutes, until tender.
Serves 6.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: First combine ingredients for sauce including onion and pepper; set aside.
Now take hamburger and oatmeal and mix together.
Take some of the sauce and add to meat mix, just enough to mix easy.
Roll into small balls, the longer you roll and work the balls, the more likely they'll be to stay together.
Put in crock-pot on high until boiling.
Turn down to low and simmer all day.
This is also good with party franks, the key for good taste is time.
So let them cook for as long as possible.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil hen and debone.
In butter, fry onion, diced up chicken and cream cheese.
Place 1 tablespoon chicken in oiled tortilla shells, roll up and lay in greased baking dish; cut Monterey Jack cheese up over layered shells.
Cover with whipped cream and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350° and uncovered 30 minutes until brown.

title: green split pea soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven (heavy large saucepan), add peas to the water along with ham bone, pepper and salt. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour. Add vegetables and garlic and simmer for another hour. Remove ham bone and chop meat fine. Discard bone and return meat to soup. Add milk, broth and sliced franks and simmer 30 minutes more. Add salt if necessary. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Mix together sugar, water, corn syrup and salt in 2-quart casserole.
Loosely cover with a lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until boiling.
Uncover and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into logs.
Put pecan pieces in a pie pan and roll cheese logs in pecans.
Wrap in Reynolds Wrap and age 3 days.
Serve with Hi-Ho crackers.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Mix together; beat on medium-high for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° for 38 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: easy russian ancheenki
directions: Saute ingredients in water.
Roll out dough on floured board to 1/4 inch or less.
Cut circles with large mouth canning ring. Place a tablespoon of cabbage mixture on 1 side of circle.
Fold over and seal.
Allow to rise in oven on lowest heat until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold. Great with soup.
Makes about 50 Ancheenki.
Goes with Whole Wheat Bread.

title: heath bar cake
directions: After cake bakes, poke holes in cake with a straw.
Mix caramel topping and Eagle Brand milk together.
Pour over cake. Sprinkle Heath bars over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with crushed Heath bars and chopped nuts.

title: miracle brownies(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter will be somewhat stiff.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Microwave on High power for 6 minutes.
Use carousel or raise pan from floor of oven and give 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.
Best when frozen before cutting.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Mix cocoa, salt, vanilla, and powdered sugar. Add coffee; Add enough to make the mixture the right consistency to spread. Add the melted butter. Sprinkle chopped nuts on the top and sides of the cake.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Trim ends of zucchini and slice in halves lengthwise.
Boil in salted water until tender (about 4 minutes).
Mix zucchini and onion and add remaining ingredients.
Use 1 1/2-quart casserole; use more croutons or bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: mixed pear slaw
directions: Drain pears, reserving 4 teaspoons pear liquid; chop pears. Combine cabbages, chopped pears, carrots and onion in medium bowl. Combine mayonnaise, reserved pear liquid, dill, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add dressing to cabbage mixture; toss to mix. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Mix together cookies and butter.
Press 2/3 cup of crumbs in pan.
Add creme de menthe to Marshmallow Fluff.
Add whipped cream.
Pour into crumb lined pan.
Top with remaining crumbs. Put into freezer.

title: lemon-lime vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: jean's banana cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs, milk, pudding and 1 cup of bananas for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour in 2- 9 inch pans or a 9 inch x 13 inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes and flip on cookie sheet.
Freeze for at least 12 hours.
To make icing, cream shortening, add 10X sugar, salt, vanilla and enough banana to hold a stiff consistency for icing.
Ice the cake while frozen.

title: sausage and acorn squash bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown the sausage (as you would ground beef).
Drain grease.
Slice squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Combine rice, hot water, onion, margarine, salt and pepper in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Mix in sausage and carrots.
Place the four squash halves on top of the sausage/rice mixture with the shell side up.
Cover pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes until the squash is tender.
I also make this using 1 cup of wild rice and 1 cup of regular rice.
Since the wild rice takes longer to cook, I cook it in the microwave for 10 minutes in 1 cup of water while I'm getting the rest of the ingredients ready. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, salt, cinnamon and cloves in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in orange and apple.
Pour into mold.
Chill 4 hours.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Pat into 9-inch square pan. Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (no more, maybe less) until top is firm.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Remove from pan when completely cool.

title: stir 'n roll biscuits
directions: Stir together ingredients until dough cleans side of the bowl and forms a ball 1-inch thick.
Knead dough 4 times, roll out and cut out.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch ungreased biscuit pan and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix top 6 ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in pecans and let set for 8 hours.
Roll in parsley and set 14 more hours, 24 hours total.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: In a large soup pot, boil chicken broth, celery, carrots and onions for approximately 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, olive oil, tomatoes, spinach (thaw and re-chop finer), lemon juice, Italian seasoning, garlic and wine.
Add prepared meatballs last and simmer for about 1 hour.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese on top.
(If using homemade meatballs, cook them before adding to soup.)

title: chicken ziti
directions: Put olive oil in frying pan to cover chicken (which has been cut into small or medium pieces).
Also can add oleo to olive oil and add chopped garlic.
Cook on medium heat until chicken is done. Steam broccoli.
Cook Ziti shells.
Add all together with cheese. Ready to eat!

title: chocolate peanut butter truffles
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with butter. Stir in cocoa until smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Cook and stir until thickened and well blended, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Chill 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in finely chopped nuts, unsweetened cocoa, graham cracker crumbs, coconut or powdered sugar.
Chill again until firm.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, then in separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Combine and mix just until moist. Pour into microwavable tube baking dish.
Cook on Medium for 9 minutes, then on High for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Remove spices. Serve warm.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish, draining beans and water chestnuts. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spuds a la elegant
directions: Blend softened cream cheese into potatoes.
Add egg, onion, pimento salt and pepper.
Bake in 1-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients, blending well.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with oil, vanilla, sugar and zucchini.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts or raisins. Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center tests done.

title: scampi
directions: Combine oil and garlic in oval microproof baking dish just large enough to hold all ingredients.
Cook on High 1 minute. Stir in minced parsley, wine and paprika.
Cook on High 1 minute. Add shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper; stir to coat well.
Arrange shrimp with tails toward center of dish. Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Stir; cover. Cook on High 1 minute.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: mom's patio casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Melt butter or margarine.
Brown meat, breaking into bite size pieces; drain.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup, flour and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes over low heat.
In separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, sour cream, salt and vegetables.
Place 1/2 noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cottage cheese mixture.
Top with rest of noodles.
Finally, spread meat mixture over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 12 hearty servings.

title: aunt alice's olive oil pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers thin.
Mix in
1 1/2 cups coarse salt and let stand 3 hours.
Slice onions; salt and let stand 3 hours. Mix other ingredients.
Pour mixture over pickles and onions that have been drained; stir well.
Pack in sterilized jars and cover with pure cider vinegar and seal.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and then other ingredients, stirring in salted peanuts last.
Drop by spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until lightly browned and appear crisp.
Remove to brown paper to cool.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and roll chicken in flour.
Put melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan and cover with milk.
Bake until tender, turning so that it browns on both sides.
You'll find this is a change and delicious.
Makes its own gravy.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add together and simmer. Serves 25 people.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Fold in 1 cup flour. Add vanilla and lemon.
Mix remaining cup of flour with fruit and nuts. Add to cake mixture.
Use Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: In a large saucepan, cover sweet potatoes with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate layers of potatoes and apples in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour orange juice over.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Place frozen broccoli on double layer of paper towel and microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain.
Combine by hand with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares to serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Beat in egg.
Stir together flour, soda and dash of salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill 10 minutes.
Using half the dough at a time, force through cookie press on ungreased cookie sheet.
If desired, sprinkle with finely chopped peanuts.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: beauty parlor pie
directions: Line casserole (13 x 2-inch pan) with 1/2 of crackers.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and milk together.
Spread over crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Top with chocolate frosting and chill overnight.

title: rice vegetable salad
directions: Cook rice in dressing and water.
Combine all other ingredients and mix with rice.
Chill before serving.
Serves 10.

title: millionaire dollar pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and remaining ingredients.
Must be refrigerated.
Garnish with chopped cherries and nuts if desired.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Add apples and nuts, mix until all is moist. Bake in greased bread pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add 2 egg yolks and beat well.
Add bananas, combine flour with soda and salt, add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and nuts; fold in 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° in two 9-inch cake pans for 30 minutes. Frost with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cook rice according to package.
Let cool. Whip the whipping cream to stiff peaks; add sugar to taste.
Add to rice.
Combine mixture with pineapple and cherries.
Fold in marshmallows, if you wish.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Add melted margarine to cookies.
Press into 9-inch pie pan. Reserve 1 teaspoon crumbs.
Chill.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; add eggs, beating well.
Add soda and cream of tartar to flour.
Sift into mixture.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cookie cutter ornaments
directions: Cover your table with a plastic sheet.
Put shaving cream on the table for kids to smush around.
Add drops of food coloring here and there.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, cinnamon and flour; reserve 3 tablespoons of mixture. Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Add egg. Add buttermilk mixture to remaining flour mixture. Beat just enough to mix well. Stir in apples and nuts. Pour in greased 9 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle top with reserved flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: nutty clusters
directions: Partially melt chocolate in saucepan over very low heat. Remove from heat; stir rapidly until entirely melted.
Add nuts and mix lightly until completely coated with chocolate.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Store, covered, in cool place.
Makes about 2 dozen confections.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak in saucepan.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Place steak in large roasting pan. Pour sauce over meat.
Cover tightly and bake in moderate oven (325°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: mini italian meat loaves
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
In large bowl, combine reserved tomato liquid with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
On baking sheet, shape into six 1-inch thick patties. Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done. Makes 6 servings.

title: clever juday frosting
directions: Melt the chocolate.
In a bowl sift the confectioners sugar and add the egg, milk, vanilla, softened butter and melted chocolate. Beat 5 minutes.
Spread on cake, cookies or cupcakes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops front and back with Creole seasoning and garlic powder. Saute chops in oil and put aside. Mix water, soup and rice, place in a baking dish. Lay pork chops on top of this mixture. Slice tomatoes, pepper and onion to form round slices and place on top of pork chops. Cover with aluminum foil and bake about one hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter clusters(candy)
directions: Just let the sugar and Karo syrup come to a boil.
Immediately add peanut butter.
Mix and stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: chicken fritters
directions: Cut chicken off bone and cut into pieces about 1 inch square. Set aside.
Mix together dry ingredients and liquids in separate bowls.
Roll chicken in liquid, then in dry ingredients.
Deep fry in hot oil until puffy and golden, about 6 to 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, soup and onion in 9 x 9-inch square pan. Spread out; put Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Note:
Peach or orange yogurt may be substituted for pineapple yogurt.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in a double broiler.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and coloring.

title: garden patch pasta salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Drain . In a large bowl, combine macaroni, zucchini, red pepper, bacon, eggs and seasoning; mix lightly.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine cheese, mayonnaise, milk and mustard; stir over low heat until cheese spread is melted.
Combine with elbow macaroni mixture; toss lightly.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken-spinach manicotti
directions: Saute mushrooms in olive oil over high heat, stirring frequently.
Add chopped chicken and spinach and remove from heat. Set aside to cool while cooking the manicotti or lasagna in boiling water.
When just tender, drain and rinse in cool water.
Finish filling noodles and roll up or use a teaspoon to stuff each tube of manicotti.
Place in an oiled 11 x 7-inch shallow baking dish. Have oven heated to 375°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge
cut
up fruit in flour and mix all ingredients. Bake on
greased cookie sheet in a slow oven at 250° approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: almond hershey bar cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and chocolate syrup.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and melted candy bars.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
As soon as you take it out of the pan, wrap it in aluminum foil.
(Cake will steam itself and be moister.)

title: pecan loaf
directions: Grind together.
Bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and scrub them.
Dice in fairly large pieces. Fry in very hot oil until almost done.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic powder and chili powder and cook until done.
Drain oil off and add taco sauce.
Cook a few minutes longer, stirring to mix sauce in.
You can sprinkle grated cheese over the top if you want to.
It's very good.

title: chicken and shrimp stir-fry
directions: Boil Oriental noodles and vegetables in a pot.
Cut chicken breasts in small strips.
Saute chicken and shrimp in margarine in a skillet.
Cook on medium or until chicken strips are done. After meat has simmered, mix it with Oriental noodles and vegetables or pour on top of rice and add soy sauce.

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Perk water, tea bags, cloves and cinnamon sticks in coffee pot.
Add sugar, orange, lemon and pineapple juices.

title: sausage balls
directions: Lightly brown sausage and drain well.
Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Melt margarine and cream cheese until you can cream well.
Add sugar, coconut and vanilla; cream well.
Spread on each layer of cake and the rest on top.

title: spoon bread
directions: Melt butter in large bowl; stir in beaten eggs and sour cream. Add corn and muffin mix.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: In large bowl, measure all ingredients except gumdrops.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in gumdrops.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until lightly brown in a 350° oven.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Combine soup, mushrooms with liquid, sour cream and cooking sherry.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch greased dish; pour mixture over it.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serve with fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: cheese sausage pinwheels
directions: Separate rolls into 8 rectangles.
Spread sausage over rectangles.
Top with grated cheese.
Roll up into rolls (jelly roll style).
Chill thoroughly in refrigerator.
Slice into 1/2-inch or 1-inch slices. Place in muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and fennel seed; drain.
Cut muffins in half and put on cookie sheet.
Put 1 teaspoon pizza sauce on muffins. Put hamburger and Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Put cookie sheet in broiler; cook until cheese is brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend the cream cheese, powdered sugar, oleo and vanilla together; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip, then fold in cream cheese mixture.
Starting with crumbs, layer into any container (clay flowerpot lined with foil, plastic sand pail, etc.).
Hide gummy worms in among layers as you go.
Decorate with flowers (real or artificial), wrapping in foil before "planting."

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Mix butter with soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Lay frozen hash browns in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Add all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate cocoa mix cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cocoa and cocoa mix. Add vinegar, vanilla and cooking oil. Slowly add 1 cup cold water. Pour into greased and floured 8-inch pan or 12 cupcakes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: parmesan rice with shrimp
directions: In a large saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon butter. Add oil, celery and green onions.
Saute over medium heat until golden, but not brown. Stir in rice and broth. Bring to a boil. Cover and cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or according to rice package directions.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush Pecan Sandies and add melted oleo; mix together.
Put crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (could take a little longer).

title: old fashioned chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine chicken broth and chicken in heavy large pot. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover partially and simmer until chicken is cooked, about 20 minutes. Using tongs, transfer chicken to large bowl. Cool chicken and broth slightly. Discard skin and bones from chicken. Cut chicken into bite size pieces and reserve. Spoon fat off chicken broth. Return broth to simmer. Add onion, carrots and celery. Simmer until vegetables soften, about 8 minutes. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms and saute about 5 minutes. Stir in lemon juice. Add mushrooms to broth. Stir in noodles, parsley and reserved chicken. Simmer until noodles are tender, about 8 minutes. Season soup to taste with salt and pepper. Serves 12.

title: corn meal tortillas
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt. Stir in shortening and boiling water. Shape to form 12 balls.
Roll out and press between wax paper to make 5-inch circles.
Bake on hot grill.

title: gavin's gorgeous cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, melted butter, cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/4 cup of sugar in a bowl.
Mix well.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and pat the crumb mixture over the bottom and up the sides.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Thicken 2 cups chicken broth with flour.
Mix cooked noodles, chicken, pimento and soup.
Pour thickened broth over mixture. Add milk and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cini-mini rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Unroll rolls into 4 rectangles. Spread each evenly with butter. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle this over buttered rectangles. Roll them up and slice each one into five rolls. Place sliced side down on cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until golden, at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 100 balls. Freeze any unused until needed.

title: lamb on the rod white sauce
directions: Clean and section peppers, removing stems and seeds.
Place in blender with all other ingredients.
Blend until it becomes the consistency of paste.

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Combine flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and margarine; add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in apple.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups or line with paper bake cups; fill 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with nut mixture. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: yogurt bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg whites slightly in medium bowl. Mix in oil and yogurt. Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pan. Makes 1 dozen muffins. Contains 6 grams fat per muffin.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Put rice in a saucepan and add cold water to cover by 3/4-inch.
Bring to a boil, uncovered.
Turn the heat down to low, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let it stand, covered, for at least 10 to 15 minutes.
While rice is cooking, heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until it is hot, but not smoking.
Add shrimp and saute for 3 minutes, moving the pan continuously to avoid sticking or burning. With a slotted spoon, remove cooked shrimp and set aside.
Turn heat down to medium-low and add garlic, chestnuts, coconut milk, fish sauce, pepper flakes, minced onion, lime juice and curry mix. Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add cornstarch paste and simmer for 5 more minutes, until mixture thickens. Put shrimp back into the sauce along with cilantro and half the sliced green onion.
Simmer for 3 more minutes.
Transfer to a heated serving bowl and garnish with remaining sliced green onion.
Makes 5 servings.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Sift with baking powder, soda and salt. Cream the butter; add sugar gradually, creaming all the while. Add Egg Beaters.
Mash bananas; add to mixture.
Blend in well. Stir in dry ingredients gradually until well blended.
Turn into loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) from 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand in pan a few minutes, then remove to cool.

title: reduced calorie whipped topping
directions: Pour evaporated skim milk into a metal mixing bowl; place in freezer until ice crystals form around the edges.

Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small saucepan and let stand one minute. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until gelatin dissolves. Chill until the mixture resembles the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat for 5 minutes or until peaks form.
Add gelatin, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Yield: 3 cups.
Per 1 tablespoon serving: 5 calories, trace of sodium and trace of cholesterol.
Exchange: Up to 4 tablespoons free.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni in water 25 minutes or until done.
Add bell pepper, olives and artichoke hearts.
Mix mayonnaise and marinade and add to salad.
Mix well.

title: cool summer fruit pleaser
directions: Drain pineapple, keep syrup for the filling.
Heat syrup on low with cornstarch, flour and sugar.
Whisk together and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in the vinegar.
Cool sauce and add pineapple chunks, mini marshmallows and your choice of sliced fruits.
Place in a container.
Refrigerate and enjoy at your next picnic!

title: sourdough bread, starter and feeder
directions: Mix dry yeast with 1/2 cup of the warm water.
Combine sugar, remaining 1 cup warm water and potato flakes.
Stir.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir.
Loosely cover with foil or plastic wrap for a couple of air holes punched in it.
Let stand all day.
Refrigerate that night.
After 3 days, take out and feed.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions and spread in pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla and add to the top of the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, then frost with pudding made with milk.
Fold into Cool Whip and spread on top of cake.
Refrigerate cake.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix well and chill.
This salad can be made and stored overnight in refrigerator.

title: date krispy balls
directions: Put margarine, sugar, dates and coconut into boiler and cook slowly for 6 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Cool slightly and add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, the nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Into a large bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Cut in Snowdrift shortening.
Add eggs, milk and bananas; mix well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 1 (9-inch) loaf.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Place sausage, together with cheese and bread, in shallow casserole dish.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Place in refrigerator overnight or at least 6 hours before serving.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat balls and rice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with 1/2 cup of the tomato juice. Make into balls according to desired size, 18 or more.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Pour into sterile canning jars.
Refrigerate for a few weeks.

title: easy "punch"
directions: Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Stir.
Makes 33 cups punch.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust:
Pat rolls in an 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Place all ingredients in pan and cook down approximately 20 minutes.
Make sure cabbage is still firm and not mushy.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix water and Eagle Brand milk with mixer.
Add instant pudding mix.
Chill about 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer with cookies and sliced strawberries.
Repeat pudding, cookies and strawberries. End with pudding.
(Good with peaches or other fresh fruit.)

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jelly in 2 cups hot water.
Add pie filling and undrained pineapple and stir.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish to congeal.
Beat remaining ingredients together and spread over congealed salad.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Peel and slice turnips.
Cook in salted water.
Drain and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Brown ham slightly and add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually while stirring.
Cook until thick.
Stir in soup.
Pour sauce over turnips and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini & pineapple bread
directions: Beat vigorously together the first 3 ingredients; add vanilla and grated zucchini.
Measure dry ingredients and mix together before adding to egg mix.
Drain pineapple.
Beat eggs and add pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Divide into 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Insert toothpick into center of loaves. If no dough sticks to the toothpick, the loaf is done.

title: sour milk coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan. Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt alternately with sour milk.
Flavor with vanilla and nutmeg.
If you want crumbs on top of cake, take out 1/3 cup of mixture before adding milk.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together Crisco, cocoa and sugar. Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla. Beat well, then add all dry ingredients and nuts. Pour into a well-greased pan and bake in a 350° oven.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken in dish. Top each piece of chicken with cheese. Mix soup with water and pour over cheese.
Cook stuffing according to box directions, then spoon on top of soup. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Combine green beans and onion slices in casserole.
Heat vinegar, water and sugar until mixture boils, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add salad oil and pour over.
Season with salt, pepper and Accent; toss gently.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: pork chops in cider
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook pork chops in margarine until browned on both sides.
Remove to plate.
In drippings remaining in skillet, over medium heat, cook apples and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove to a bowl. Return pork chops to skillet.
Add apple cider, bouillon, sage and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Return apples and onion to skillet.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until pork chops are tender.
With a slotted pancake turner, remove pork chops and apple quarters to a large platter.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Mix corn, broccoli, 1/2 cup crackers, 2 tablespoons butter, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with a mixture of remaining crackers and butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: glae's favorite dip
directions: Heat chili until hot.
Mix in cream cheese until melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well.
Chill for handling, if necessary.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and taco seasoning.
Layer taco shells on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to cover (approximately 4).
Top with refried beans, ground beef mixture, tomatoes and cheese.
Layer until gone ending with taco shells on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or microwave until warm.
Top with sour cream, lettuce, olives and taco sauce.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs, then stir in half of dry ingredients.
Blend milk and remaining dry ingredients. Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: turkey smoked sausage rice skillet
directions: Cut sausage
into
serving
size
pieces and set aside. Saute mushrooms and zucchini in butter for 3 minutes.
Add all ingredients except	rice.
Simmer 5 minutes covered.
Mix rice in liquid; cover
and	remove from heat.
Let stand 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Serve turkey mixture over hot rice. Serves 4.

title: new mexican quiche
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and toss lightly.
Sprinkle about 3/4 of mixture over pie shell.
Heat milk in measuring cup on high 2 1/2 minutes.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Add hot milk and beat again.
Pour evenly into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining bacon mixture.
Cook at 60% power until center is barely set, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges and serving.

title: strawberry roll
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat sugar until very thick and light colored.
Fold in sifted dry ingredients.
Bake on greased cookie sheet lined and greased again.
Turn out on towel dusted well with confectioners sugar.
Roll up and cool a few minutes.
Unroll and spread with whipped cream.
Sprinkle sliced strawberries on and roll as jelly roll.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Just before serving, garnish with whole strawberries.

title: chinese sesame chicken kabobs
directions: Cut chicken breasts into thin strips.
Mix with soy sauce, oil, garlic and ginger.
Let sit 15 minutes or refrigerate overnight. Thread onto skewers.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes, turning once.
Serve over rice with sweet and sour sauce for dipping.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat; brown in hot oil, then cook onion and garlic until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients adding to meat.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to mixture. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter and set aside.
Combine cream cheese, milk, dried beef, garlic salt, sour cream and onions.
Mix thoroughly and place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fluffy 5 minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients in the top of double boiler.
Beat at speed No. 2 until well mixed, then at speed No. 9 for 4 or 5 minutes or until mixture forms a firm peak.
Remove and add vanilla.
Very good for cookies or cakes.
Add colored coconut or sprinkles for decoration.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Put potatoes (still frozen) in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mixture of sour cream, onion, cheese, soup and margarine.
Crush 1 1/2 cups corn flakes with 1/3 cup melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° covered.
Take cover off the last 15 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: 3 layer brownies
directions: 1st Layer:
Make brownies according to package directions, except add chocolate bits and coconut. Bake and cool.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix well together.
Pour into pie pan.
Cook quickly at 400°. Makes 2 pies.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, Crisco, butter, vanilla and half of the cake mix until smooth, then stir in remaining cake mix until smooth.
Roll dough out and cut any desired shape or square. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Poke fork holes in when fresh out of oven. Put ice cream between and freeze.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add salt. Add macaroni and boil for 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat the eggs, vanilla, flour, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: flavored tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container. To drink, mix 2 teaspoons of tea mix into 8 ounces of hot water. Serve warm or iced.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter. Beat eggs for 5 minutes with salt. Add sugar, vanilla, flour and nuts. Bake 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: bark candy (microwave)
directions: Break candy in squares.
Place in a single layer in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 4 to 7 minutes or until coating can be stirred smooth, stirring once or twice.
Add nuts. Stir to evenly coat; spread on wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness. Cool until set, then break into pieces.

title: tomato chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onions and celery. Cook over low heat until tender. Drain corn and beans. Reserve liquid and add water to measure 5 cups.
Add vegetables. Cook 30 minutes.
Add last beans, corn and tuna.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stir and roll biscuits
directions: Into mixing bowl place flour, baking powder and salt.
Do not stir.
Pour oil and milk on top.
With a fork stir until mixture clears the sides of the bowl and rounds up into a ball.

title: hallelujah halibut
directions: Rinse halibut and pat dry.
Arrange steaks, side by side, in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream and flour, stirring until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, onion and cayenne.
Spoon mixture evenly over fish to cover completely.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until fish is opaque in center of thickest part.
Sprinkle cheese over fish; continue to bake until cheese is just melted, about 2 minutes.
Lift steaks onto warmed platter and serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the first 4 items in the order given.
Then spread sour cream over the top, then crumbs from the beefsteak rye bread.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion in a frying pan.
Drain fat. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix macaroni with pizza sauce.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Put meat in baking pan.
Add green beans and soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuit sausage quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Drain well.
Combine eggs, cheese and sausage mixture.
Separate dough into 8 biscuits.
Press biscuits into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sausage mixture into biscuit lined pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until quiche is set and crust is deep golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: busy day chicken and mushrooms(for crock-pot)
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot.
Sprinkle dry salad mix over. Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
About 45 minutes before serving, mix soup, cream cheese, sherry and onions in a small saucepan.
Cook until smooth.
Pour over chicken along with mushrooms.
Cook 30 more minutes on low.
Serve with sauce over rice or noodles.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, onions, salt and pepper together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix spaghetti sauce with mushroom soup.
Pour over meat loaf.
Return to oven.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Line cake pan with foil. Combine almonds, butter, sugar and syrup in iron frypan.
Cook mixture until light brown (6 to 8 minutes), stirring constantly. Quickly spread in foil lined cake pan. Cool 15 minutes. Remove from foil.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Arrange peach slices in unbaked pie shell.
Beat together sugar, flour and eggs.
Pour over peaches.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until peaches are tender, about 1 hour.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven or large pot.
Cover and bake at 225° for 5 to 6 hours.
No stirring is necessary.
Serve with rice or noodles or in bowls as is.

title: nancy's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; let set 20 minutes.
Mix oil, buttermilk and sugar.
Sift rest of ingredients.
Add yeast to buttermilk mixture and then add sifted ingredients to it, mixing well.
Pour out on floured board and knead for about 20 minutes or until it has an elastic texture.
Put in large well-greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Separate into small rolls on greased baking sheets until double in size.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 20 minutes.

title: angel sherbet refrigerator cake
directions: Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Break cake in chunks and arrange cake and scoops of sherbet and ice cream in layers in an angel food pan.
Fill cavities with whipped cream.
Also spread between layers.
Freeze and slice and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and bake in Pyrex dish at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve with Melba toast or Chicken-in-Biscuit crackers.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour baking pans and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, place flour, leaving a depression in the center.
Place butter and buttermilk in the depression and start mixing by hand with flour.
Knead together, adding more milk and butter if dough is too stiff.
Dough should be moist.
Roll handful of dough into ball.
Flour outside and place in baking pan.
Pat down.
Repeat until all dough is used or until desired amount of biscuits are made.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush tops with melted butter.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl and pour lemon-lime soda over top. Add ice.
Yield: Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan.
Cream the butter, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually add flour; blend until thoroughly mixed.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn cake out onto cooling rack and cool to room temperature.

title: fruit fizz
directions: Combine the juice of the oranges and lemons; add the pineapple juice (preferably unsweetened, canned) and the cherries with their juice. Just before serving, add the white grape juice.
Turn over ice cubes and garnish each glass with a mint sprig.
Serves 8.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix and add 2% milk to fill the can.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place vanilla wafers and margarine in blender or processor and form crumb mixture.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix pudding with milk per package directions.
Pour over crumbs. Spread strawberry pie filling over pudding.
Spoon pineapple over this.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle top with nuts. Chill.
Just before serving, top with bananas (sliced) and top with cherries.

title: bacon cheese appetizer
directions: Line a microwave-safe baking dish or plate with double layers of paper towels.
Place bacon slices on dish. Cover with paper towels. Microwave on High power for about 3 minutes.
Prepare cheese cubes.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Wrap bacon around each cube. Secure with toothpicks.
Place on paper towel in a microwave-safe baking dish.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes until cheese starts to melt and bacon is done to your liking. Garnish with tomato halves and serve. Serves 4.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 3 or 4 qt. pan over low heat. Remove from heat and let cool. Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Sift together flour, soda and cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt. Add to first mixture, mix well and put in refrigerator to chill. When ready to bake, form in 1 inch balls. Roll in sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Add raisins (soak in hot water and drain first).
Mix egg and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Turn onto floured board and knead 2 to 3 minutes. Divide dough in half. Shape into loaves.
In 8-inch round pans, press dough to fill pans.
With a sharp knife, cut crosses on tops about 1/2-inch deep in the middle. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spicy apple cider
directions: Heat cider in crock-pot or on stove with all ingredients combined.
Serve hot.
Tastes best after several hours of simmering on low heat or in crock-pot.
Also provides great aroma for your kitchen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn back to 275° for 30 more minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add nuts, oats and chocolate chips. Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: buffalo chicken wing dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, hot sauce and celery.
Heat in microwave until cream cheese is melted.
Add chicken and cheese. Mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with crackers or pita bread chips.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix well by hand. Pour into greased 9 x 10 pan. Do not flour pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool, leave cake in pan.

title: california stuffed bell peppers
directions: Remove stem end, seeds and membrane from peppers.
Cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine seasoning mix, tomato and water.
Add beef and corn.
Combine thoroughly. Lightly pack into peppers.
Combine crackers and butter together. Sprinkle over top of stuffed peppers.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, or microwave about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Prepare baked pastry shell.
Mix cornstarch, flour, the 1 cup sugar and salt in top of a double boiler.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Beat egg yolks slightly and gradually stir into cornstarch mixture.
Place top of double boiler over boiling water and cook about 5 minutes until filling is thickened, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook 5 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Remove from boiling water.
Mix in butter, lemon peel and juice.
Cover and cool slightly.
Pour into pastry shell. Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add the 6 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue over lemon filling to edge of crust.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: "cheezy squares"
directions: Cream together Old English cheese, egg, chopped pepper and margarine.
Spread on slices of bread.
Cut in quarters and cover top and sides with spread.
Top with small square of partially cooked bacon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Better if frozen first.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of 8-inch square pan with Pam.
Melt butter and chocolate together (I use the microwave). Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla 5 minutes.
Add chocolate, butter mixture.
Blend in flour with spoon; add nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°; cool and cut into squares.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: *Can substitute 1 pound ground beef.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish (or Tupperware mold) and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together except biscuits.
Divide biscuits in half, making 2 full size biscuits out of one.
Press into greased muffin tin.
Fill with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sister's chili
directions: Fry meat and onions together.
Drain chili sauce off kidney beans.
Mix all rest of ingredients, minus chili sauce, and heat up.
This chili can be frozen.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Chill before serving.

title: my great-grandmother's raw fried potato cakes
directions: *My great-grandmother used to pare the potatoes, then grate them.
My mother found it far easier to put the potatoes through a fine food chopper.
If the skins are not tough, scrub them and do not peel.

title: chinese green pepper steak
directions: Heat the oil, garlic and ginger in a skillet.
Add sirloin to the ingredients and brown.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add the onions and green peppers.
Cook about 3 to 5 minutes and then add water chestnuts and steak and allow to simmer.
Add the dissolved bouillon cube, soy sauce and dissolved cornstarch.
Cook a few minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and taco sauce to hamburger.
Simmer.
Then add beans and simmer until juice evaporates.
Fill large bowl with lettuce and Doritos (slightly crushed).
Pour on dressing.
Put meat mixture on and top with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Heat juice and broth to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in gelatin until completely dissolved.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix until smooth.
Add pineapple, chicken and celery.
Pour into 2-quart mold and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cooking spray, in a container of electric blender.
Process until smooth.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pint of sauce for 5 pounds of pork ribs.

title: roasted vegetables and pasta
directions: Wash vegetables; slice thick.
Combine remaining ingredients (except pasta) in a large bowl with vegetables.
Toss to coat. Spread on a cookie sheet.
Place in a 425° oven for 30 minutes. Cook 12 ounces pasta according to package directions.
Rinse.
Mix with roasted vegetables.
Sprinkle with:

title: basic "scratch" cake
directions: Cream butter in a mixing bowl and gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat eggs one at a time.
Separately mix dry ingredients and gradually alternate dry mixture, milk and vanilla mixture.
Mix until well blended.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken; set aside.
Cook noodles; drain.
Return noodles to pan; add cream cheese, sour cream, broth, soup, onion and seasonings.
Stir.
Add the chicken.
Place all in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, covered.
Add croutons and cheese the last 15 minutes.
Remove lid during that time.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins, caraway seed, buttermilk (gradually) and egg.
Stir until blended. Knead on floured board until smooth, about 1 minute.
(Add more flour, if sticky.)
Shape dough into 2 balls and place in 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Flatten to fill pans.
Cut a deep cross in top of each loaf.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° about 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: berry frozen yogurt
directions: In a small saucepan soften gelatin in the water for 5 minutes. Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Stir together yogurt, berries, gelatin mixture, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Turn mixture into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Cover and freeze for 45 to 60 minutes or until partially frozen around the edges.
In small mixer bowl beat egg whites until soft peaks form (tips curl over).
