Gradually add the 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Turn the frozen mixture into a large mixer bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer until nearly smooth.
Fold the egg whites into berry mixture. Return to pan.
Cover and freeze for 4 to 6 hours or until firm. Scoop to serve.
Per serving:
99 calories, 1 g fat and 3 mg cholesterol.

title: five layer dessert
directions: Mix together flour, melted butter and pecans.
Press in pan (9 x 13-inches) and bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix all four ingredients together.
Dip peeled shrimp into mixture and then roll in cracker crumbs and fry.
Use blender to make cracker crumbs.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Separate each roll into 5 pieces.
Roll between 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Press into greased miniature muffin tin.
Brown sausage. Drain and spoon equally into muffin tin over rolls.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese, chives, pepper and Parmesan cheese together.
Spoon over sausage and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned.

title: western beans
directions: Lightly fry bacon.
Add onion and saute, drain.
In large pot, mix rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring once or twice. Remove bay leaf before serving.
May be prepared ahead of time, refrigerated and reheated before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: batter bread
directions: Mix altogether, pour into greased muffin pans. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 min.

title: moist chocolate fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix as for cake.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Brown sausage, onion, garlic and peppers in skillet; drain well.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Press into pan.
Mix the powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese together.
Pour on top of the cake mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti with spring vegetables
directions: Trim both ends from each of medium zucchini and cut the zucchini lengthwise in half.
Cut the halves lengthwise into quarters.
Cut zucchini pieces across into 3/8-inch chunks.
Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to a boil.
Add the zucchini and cook until barely tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain zucchini; rinse with cold water and leave to drain thoroughly.
Cut carrots into chunks like the zucchini.
Put into saucepan; cover with cold water.
Add salt and bring to a boil.
Simmer until carrots are just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain; rinse with cold water and leave to drain thoroughly.
Set aside.
Bring a saucepan of salted water to a boil.
Add the peas and simmer until tender, 3 to 8 minutes.
Drain, rinse and let drain again.
Set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Trim flower ends of baby zucchini.
Cut lengthwise into 4 to 5 slices, leaving attached at stem end.
Butter a baking sheet.
Set zucchini on sheet; sprinkle with salt and pepper and cover with buttered foil.
Bake in heated oven until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Flatten each sliced zucchini with thumb and finger to make a fan shape; keep them warm.
Fill large pot with water; bring to boil and add 1 tablespoon salt.
Add the spaghetti and simmer until tender, but still chewy, 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain; rinse with hot water and drain again.
While cooking spaghetti, finish sauce.
Heat butter in a large saucepan; add zucchini and carrot chunks and the peas and saute 1 minute.
Add the cream; stir well to mix and heat until simmering.
Take pan from heat; add drained spaghetti and toss to mix.
Add the Parmesan and toss gently.
Garnish with zucchini fan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Turn out of pan and cool. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill well. Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: milky way pound cake
directions: Melt candy bars in a Pyrex measuring cup in microwave.
This takes about 1 minute.
Stir until smooth.
Add cream and stir until smooth.
Microwave about 30 seconds more.
Immediately pour over cake.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Shred corned beef and stir in to mixture.
Cut top of bread in circle and dig out inside of bread.
Place dip in bread bowl.
Tear remaining bread in bite size pieces and place around "bowl" for dipping.
May want to buy extra bread.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with dressing; drizzle with one stick of butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: boiled potato dumplings
directions: Mix potatoes, flour, salt and pepper.
Add eggs.
Brown bread cubes and onions in margarine, and blend into potato mixture.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Mix flour, salt, brown sugar and 1 cup butter together and pat into a jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
In pan, heat chips, 3 tablespoons butter, water and syrup until chips are melted.
Add salted peanuts.
Spread over crust layer and bake 8 minutes more at 375°.
Loosen edges, cool before cutting.

title: goofy butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine.
Add pecans and coconut. Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and serve cold.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup of the sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Cook over direct heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into well beaten egg yolks.
Pour back into double boiler.
Place over boiling water; cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool until just warm.
Slice bananas into pie shell.
Pour cream mixture over. Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat in remaining sugar until smooth and stiff.
Spread over pie.
Bake in 400° oven for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles. Brown ground sausage; drain. Melt cheese slices over sausage and add tomato soup. Add all ingredients together and serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas, green beans and pimentos into a colander. Combine vinegar, sugar, Mazola oil, salt and pepper in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over vegetables in a bowl.
Will keep for 2 weeks or longer.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar mixtures, mixing thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows. Beat and mix well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Cook and bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
After cocoa mix has cooked, remove from heat and add.
Blend well.
Add oats last! Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil and allow to become firm.

title: christmas brew
directions: Mix together and serve hot.

title: aunt evelyn's punch
directions: Mix sugar and 4 cups of water to make syrup.
Let come to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Dissolve Jello in 1 qt. boiling water. Add 1 qt. cold water and cooked syrup.
Chill juices and mix 1 hour before serving.
Add ginger ale last in punch bowl.
Yield: 50 servings.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Heat together and mix.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour into it 1 box uncooked Minute rice and mix with fork.
Put pieces of chicken (uncooked) over that.
Sprinkle over chicken and rice the package of dry onion soup (no salt needed).
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon until tender. Add cornstarch, mix well and pour in pie shell.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about 1/2 the flour, the brown sugar, sugar, egg, baking powder, vanilla and baking soda. If desired, stir in cinnamon and cloves.
Beat in remaining flour. Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix hamburg, chopped onion, crushed saltines, milk and eggs.
Stir until blended well.
Place in baking pan and cook about 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: In pie pan, spread Philly (as crust), pour in chili, next layer peppers, then grated cheese, then sliced black olives and/or mushrooms.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: mrs. novacks tortilla triangle
directions: Place tortilla on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle cheese, bell peppers, 2 teaspoons sour cream and 1/2 cup of meat.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Flip tortilla in half; press lightly.
Cut into triangles.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and saute 5 minutes. Add green chilies. Saute 1 minute. Stir in cream cheese and chicken. Cook, stirring constantly, until cream cheese melts. Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons chicken mixture down center of each tortilla. Roll up tortillas and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese and drizzle with whipping cream. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: *Any good crumb crust may be used.

title: uncooked banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and vanilla wafers, pouring mixture of vanilla pudding mix, vanilla instant pudding mix, milk and sour cream over each layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Better if it sits over at least 24 hours before serving.

title: italian sausage-stuffed peppers
directions: Slice tops from peppers and reserve.
Remove the seeds and veins.
In boiling water, blanch the pepper shells and tops for 5 minutes, then rinse them well under cold water.
Pat them dry and set aside.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add mushrooms and clams.
Add juice from clams.
Cook until hot and it boils.
Add bread crumbs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Stuff shells and bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: speedy stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add bouillon cubes, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add chili sauce and sour cream.
Serve on hot rice or noodles.

title: applesauce
directions: Wash, peel, core and quarter apples.
Simmer, covered, in small amount of water until tender.
Press apples through sieve. Sweeten sauce to taste (about 1/2 cup sugar to four apples).
Use a small amount of salt and spices, if you desire.
Serve with meat.
Use as many apples as you'd like.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Put frozen hash browns in a greased 8 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Break up cheese and place on top of hash browns.
Melt oleo and stir in soup and milk.
Pour over cheese and hash browns. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir at least once during baking.
In the last few minutes before done, top with onion rings.

title: redeemer bread
directions: Pour 2 cups
boiling water over bran, sugar, Crisco and salt. Cool to
lukewarm.
Soften
2 packages yeast in 1/4 cup water; let stand.
Add
beaten
eggs
and
yeast
to
above mixture.
Add 2 cups whole wheat flour and 5 cups white flour. Mix well.
Let rise
1 hour.
Punch down and shape into loaves or rolls.
Let rise
1 1/2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes for loaf at 350°, rolls 15 minutes at 400°.

title: hot hors d'oeuvres
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in container and mix thoroughly, adding the water if it is necessary to make all hold together. Form into small balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles; melt butter.
Mix together all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 14-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cuts best when cooled.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: If you use frozen beans, cook and drain.
If using canned beans, just drain.
Combine beans, soup, water chestnuts and 1/4 of the onion rings.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: one hour dinner rolls
directions: Disslove yeast in warm water.
Let sit while preparing other ingredients.
Combine buttermilk, sugar, melted shortening, and salt.
Mix yeast to buttermilk mixture and add soda.
Stir in flour, one cup at a time until desired consistency.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Pull off small egg size portions and roll into a ball.
Place in oiled baking pan.
Let stand 30-45 minutes in a warm draft free place until risen.
Bake 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix rice, cream of mushroom soup, water, broccoli, onion and celery.
Pour in casserole. Spread cheese over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix chicken or turkey, vegetables, celery, mushroom or chicken soup, water or broth, salt and pepper and put in casserole dish. Top with eggs.
Spread over top with margarine, flour and milk. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Place milk, banana, ice cream and vanilla extract in a blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed and let cool.
Mix pudding and Dream Whip according to directions for Dream Pie.
Makes 8 layers.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Blend in paraffin. Mix confectioners sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla in a bowl. Shape by spoonfuls into balls around cherries.
Dip into chocolate to coat.
Place in paper bonbon cups.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: todays easy roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in bag and place in a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan, add tomatoes, soup mix and pepper.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Put in roast and turn bag to coat roast.
Close bag with tie, cut 6 slits in top and bake 1 1/2 - 2 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Dip mushrooms in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Place them cap side down in a buttered baking dish.
Combine crabmeat, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and half of bread crumbs.
Fill mushrooms with this mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill dough and shape into small balls the size of a walnut.
Press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Tap lightly with meat tenderizer for pretty design.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix together and leave overnight.

title: somen salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Chill.

title: green bean frittata
directions: Wash, drain, string and trim ends of green beans and break/cut into 2-inch pieces.
Pack tightly into hot canning jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart.
Pour in boiling water, covering beans; but leaving 1-inch headspace.
Put on caps.
Process in pressure cooker at 10 pounds pressure, pints 20 minutes and quarts 25 minutes.

title: one step meal
directions: Put all ingredients into a baking dish and bake for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef until crumbly.
Layer the noodles, layer at a time, with cheeses, sauce and hamburger.
Use more cheese if you want to.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°; depends on oven.
You can use other cheeses if you desired
or more hamburger.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Cook meal, water and milk together until it begins to thicken. Set off and cool.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Simmer onion.
Add ground meat and cook until brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder to taste and cook.

title: soft pretzels(makes 32)
directions: Warm water in large warm bowl; sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, 2 teaspoons salt, margarine, egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl tightly with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Divide in half; cut each 1/2 in 16 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into pencil shape, about 20-inches long.
Shape into pretzel.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Blend egg yolk and 2 tablespoons water.
Brush pretzel with mixture.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let rise in warm place (oven) until doubled in bulk, about 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: garbage
directions: Mix olives, tomatoes, mushrooms, onions and pepper.
Add vinegar, oil and sugar.
Let marinate for several hours.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: champagne dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Combine other ingredients together and add to sugar and cream cheese mixture.
Mix together. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut in squares.

title: soup and noodles
directions: Place soup and 1 can of water in 10-inch skillet.
Heat to a simmer.
In small bowl, carefully crack egg in half, saving shell to measure liquids.
Add 1/2 egg shell of oil and 2 half egg shells of water.
Add dash of salt; mix well.
Add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Place over simmering soup.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake(there's nothing really mexican about this. it's so good!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix, butter, 2 eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over cake layer.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: my bread and butter pickles
directions: In large glass or stainless bowl, combine cukes, onions and salt.
Let stand for 3 hours, then strain.
Rinse with cold water, and strain again.
Drain in colander.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine fruit; add flour and dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Pour over fruit.
Add nuts.
Pack in pan. Bake at 275°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: toffee apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Mix pineapple with marshmallows and set aside.
Mix pineapple juice with egg, flour, vinegar and sugar.
Microwave the mixture 6-8 minutes on high, stirring every 3 minutes.
Pour over pineapple and marshmallows. Stir in remainder of ingredients.

title: sunflower chicken stir-fry
directions: Before beginning to cook, make sure the rice is cooked and cooled and the onions, celery and carrots are chopped close to the same size (remember, stir-frying goes fast). Combine the sesame oil and garlic powder and add chicken to marinate briefly while wok or skillet is heating.
Heat electric skillet or wok to about 375° (medium-high) and add chicken.

Stir-fry chicken until thoroughly cooked, adding sunflower seeds about halfway through (after 5 to 7 minutes). Add onions, celery, carrots and 2 tablespoons soy sauce. Stir-fry to mix and add the eggs.
Continue mixing quickly.
When egg is cooked, add cold rice and remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce. Stir-fry over high heat until rice is hot.

title: spicy hot dog corn biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions, adding the red peppers, chili powder and cayenne pepper.
Spray or lightly coat a large cookie sheet with cooking oil.
Using 3/4 of the batter, drop batter by spoon into 16 to 24 mounds.
Cut hot dogs into chunks to equal number of mounds and put 1 hot dog chunk into center of each mound; top with remaining batter.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with salsa or honey.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Make jello as usual but add pineapple juice with water to make 4 cups liquid. When it is a little firm, beat the cream cheese and milk that has been chilled overnight.
Fold in cheese mixture, jello, pineapple and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: nutmeg logs
directions: Cream butter with flavorings; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift flour, 1 teaspoon nutmeg and salt.
Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Shape pieces of dough on sugared board into long rolls 1/2-inch in diameter.
Cut in 3-inch lengths and put on buttered cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Spread frosting on top and sides of cookies. Mark with tines of fork to resemble bark.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: beef and onion stew with mustard gravy
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper. Dredge meat in flour mixture.
In a Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add meat and brown well, about 5 minutes.
Remove.
Peel onions and cut into quarters.
Mince the garlic.
Add the remaining 1 tablespoon oil to pan and heat.
Add onions; saute until beginning to brown, about 10 minutes.
Stir in garlic.
Return meat to pan, along with broth, bay leaf and thyme. Cook until meat is almost tender, about 1 hour.

title: gelatin vegetable salad
directions: Place gelatin in a mold or a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Add boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add cold water.
Add celery, carrots, green pepper, radishes and onion and stir mixture.
Chill several hours until firm.

title: beck ice cream
directions: Mix well and pour into ice cream freezer.
Fill to just below the top paddle with whole milk. Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar and beat well.
Mix the mashed bananas into the sugar and shortening mixture.
Add and mix the soda, salt and baking powder, then add flour last.
Mix well. Pour into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight or eat right away!

title: goody cake
directions: Grease and flour an 11 1/2 x 17 x 2 1/4-inch pan.
Heat 1 stick butter and milk.
Beat eggs in separate bowl; add sugar and beat.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to mixture gradually.
Beat.
Pour in milk and butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 300° or until done.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Select fresh firm cucumbers, wash and pack into jars.
Add to each quart jar:
dill, garlic and peppers.
Bring to a boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour hot solution over cucumbers and seal jars. Pickles will be ready in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: pumpkin pie with graham cracker crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Bake 50 minutes at 375° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: fudge
directions: Combine together in ovenproof pan.
Place in a 250° oven until completely melted.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
(For mint flavored fudge, use mint ice cream.)

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar into a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg; add water and vinegar, add to dry ingredients in about 3 or 4 portions; toss with spoon.
Finish dough by forming ball with your hands.
This dough must be chilled before rolling.
Better if chilled at least 1 hour or more.
Will keep at least 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage, stir often.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into buttered pan, let cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Add margarine and instant potatoes.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mash other potatoes and stir constantly until soup is thickened.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: cucumber-vinegar salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin.
Add sliced onion.
Stir together vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over slices.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours (7 to 10 hours is better).
This is wonderful to serve with hamburgers at a backyard summertime picnic.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour half of the mixture in mold.
Chill.
When set spread 1/2 pint of sour cream over top. Add remaining half of mixture.
Chill.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Beat whipping cream until fluffy, even if using Cool Whip. Set aside 1/4 cup cake crumbs for top.
Divide remaining crumbs into 4 portions.
Sprinkle one portion of crumbs in bottom of a serving bowl.
In large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, spices, milk and pudding.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon half of mix on top of cake crumbs in bowl.
Sprinkle with more cake crumbs.
Put 1/2 of whipped cream on top.
Add more cake crumbs; add pumpkin mixture, then add last of crumbs.
Put on remaining whipped cream. Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs on top.
Chill at least 1 to 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: vienna chocolate bars
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add flour, kneading with fingers to form dough.
Pat dough into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread the base with jam.
Top with chocolate bits.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Fold in sugar and nuts.
Spread mixture on top of jam.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 30 bars.

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt 1/2 cup peanut butter in chocolate bar; blend until smooth.
Melt remaining 1 cup peanut butter in separate pot.

title: ground turkey pie casserole
directions: Brown turkey and onion.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add soup to drained beans, heat and pour over turkey.
Mash potatoes, add milk, egg and sesaoning.
Spoon over beans.
Dab with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil.
After it thickens, remove and add Jell-O.
Let cool.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Combine the above ingredients.
Form into pancake size patties.
Fry on both sides until they are golden brown.

title: cajun sauce piquant
directions: Put oil in a large pot; brown meat.
Add the remaining ingredients except water and flour.
Mix water and flour; add to sauce.
Let cook on low heat for 1 hour or until tender.
Stir every few minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: egg custard
directions: Put eggs in blender, then sugar.
Blend about 7 minutes on low speed.
Put milk on stove and cook until it boils.
Set it off one minute.
Repeat 3 times.
On third time, add margarine.
Add this to sugar and milk.
Blend on high speed about 7 to 8 minutes.
Pour into deep unbaked pie crust and cook for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together, stir in whole wheat flour and add to creamed mixture; mixing well.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture into pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: popcorn salad
directions: Combine celery, carrots, water chestnuts, onion and mayo. (This can be mixed a day ahead or at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.)
Just before you serve, add popcorn, bacon and cheese.

title: beef-okra soup
directions: Brown beef, pour off drippings.
Add water, sugar, salt, pepper pods and garlic.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Drain tomatoes. Combine flour with 1/4 cup tomato liquid.
Stir into beef.
Add tomatoes, remaining tomato liquid and onion.
Continue cooking, covered, 30 minutes.
Stir in corn, green pepper and okra; cook 10 to 12 minutes more.

title: carrot bake
directions: Cook carrots; add oleo.
Put cheese on top.
Put on cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown, about 20 minutes.

title: fish fry
directions: Soak the fish in milk for 1 hour.
Dip the fish into the seasoned flour.
Beat the eggs with 1/4 cup milk; add salt and pepper.
Dip the fish in this mixture.
Dip the fish in the bread crumbs.
Fry the fish in hot oil.
Brown it fast; turn it over. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hungry boy casserole(robert jr.'s favorite)
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until brown; drain.
Add Manwich, pork and beans and corn.
Heat in skillet until heated through. Place mixture in a 12 x 8-inch or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place biscuits on top of mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 or 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: bavarian torte (cheese cake)
directions: In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat butter, 1/3 c sugar and 1/4 tsp vanilla until well blended.
Gradually add flour and continue beating until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
With lightly floured hands press into a 9 inch pie plate.
In a small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and 1/4 c sugar just until smooth.
Beat in egg and 1/2 tsp vanilla until well blended.
Pour over crust.
preheat oven to 450 degrees.
In a large bowl combine sugar and cinnamon; add peach slices and toss gently.
arrange on top of cheese mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 400 degrees and bake 25 minutes longer. Serve either warm or cold.

title: mixed pepper salad
directions: Cut peppers into 1-inch squares.
Pour dressing over the combined peppers and chill 3 hours.
Drain and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: baked steak with mushrooms
directions: Cut excess fat from steak.
Flour steak and brown it lightly on both sides in butter.
Put steak in baking dish and pour gravy and mushrooms on top.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well and drop from spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, almonds, onion, olives and eggs.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.

title: divinity
directions: Mix and boil sugar, hot water and salt.
Cook until syrup reaches hard ball stage on candy thermometer.
Then pour slowly into egg whites while beating.
Add pecans.
When mixture begins to hold its shape, quickly drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until set and brown as desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix spaghetti and vegetables in a large bowl.
Pour in the salad mix and the bottle of dressing and toss very well.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Chill overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put buttered bread in bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan.
Put sausage on top of this.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over sausage. Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt
butter
in
baking dish.	Mix ingredients (except fruit or	pie filling) and pour over butter.
Add fruit or pie filling. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs; add all other ingredients except for cheese. Mix and pour into pie shell; sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: dozena's beef stew
directions: Fry stew beef in a small amount of oil until brown on all sides.
Put in a crock-pot and add potatoes, carrots, soup, water and salt.
Mix well and cook until beef is tender.

title: clam bisque
directions: Use large pot over medium heat.
Cook onion, celery, garlic, in butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add broth and potatoes. Heat to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes until potatoes are done.
Strain soup mixture, reserving liquid.
Puree 1 cup potato mixture.
Return puree to remaining mixture and liquid in pot.
Add clams and cream.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil. Top with parsley.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream together with sugar and peanut butter.
Beat in the milk and fold in the Kool Whip.
Pour mixture into pie crusts and chill.
Makes two pies.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers in salt water for 5 minutes.
Brown hamburger and onion in oil.
Mix hamburger, onion, rice, salt, pepper and egg with 1/2 can tomato soup.
Stuff peppers.
Place in baking dish. Add 1/2 can soup and 1/2 can of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Place a small piece of cheese on each pepper just before removing from oven just long enough for cheese to melt.

title: wassail
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Add fresh cranberries.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat butter or margarine with peanut butter. Add sugars. Beat until light and fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Beat until well blended. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar, if desired. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press crisscross markings with a fork. Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes or until done. Cool 1 minute. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: turnip greens
directions: Turnip greens should be thoroughly washed to be free of grit, through several waters.
Remove any objectionable part of tough stem.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over it. Sprinkle dry onion mix over it.
Cover with soup and water mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sara's cheese straws
directions: With cheese and oleo at room temperature, mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Place on pan with cookie press.
Cook in 350° oven until light brown.
If you prefer, you can roll in small ball, dip fork in flour and press ball flat.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, drain fat.
Stir in taco seasoning mix and spread in 10-inch pie plate (sprayed with Pam), top with chilies.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth. Pour on top hamburger mixture.
Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven. Remove and top with sliced tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Garnish with layer of sour cream, chopped tomatoes, shredded lettuce and shredded cheese.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, crushed pineapple, boiling water and blueberry pie filling.
Refrigerate until set.
Combine the sour cream, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over pie filling.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour Sprite over sherbet and serve.

title: hot festive punch
directions: Pour all ingredients in large pot; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Stir and serve hot.

title: green tomato cake
directions: Simmer
chopped
green tomatoes and 1/2 cup sugar until tomatoes
are
well
cooked and transparent.
Strain through a colander to
remove
the seeds, cores and skins.
There should be 1 1/4 cups pulp.
Cool.
Combine 1 cup sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Blend
in
baking soda into tomato pulp and add to sugar mixture,
beating
well.
In another bowl, combine 1 cup flour, salt
and spices.
Add to batter.
Combine raisins and nuts with 1
cup
flour.
Add to tomato batter.
Add eggs and beat
well. Pour into well-greased square cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done at 350°. Goes well with yellow rice.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend together salad dressing and cream cheese.
To the cheese mixture add sliced maraschino cherries, drained pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in mold and freeze until firm.

title: italian stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes; drain.
Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Stir in tomato sauce, rice, 1 cup cheese and oregano.
Spoon into peppers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
This is good fixed with frozen green peppers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Stir in eggs, oil and carrots.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.

title: festive fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In a large bowl combine eggs and water. Add remaining ingredients except syrup; stir by hand until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.
Glaze with warm corn syrup before serving.
Decorate with additional fruit and nuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 9 X 13 inch greased pan or casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Do not over bake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in casserole dish. Sprinkle 3/4 bag of bread crumbs in dish over butter.
Spread chicken on top.
Pour broth over chicken.
May need a little more for moister dressing.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over casserole.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Prepare and cook potatoes.
Drain, dice and chill.
Add diced celery, cucumber, olives and onion.
Toss together lightly with a fork.
Blend in Italian dressing.
Cover and chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.

title: jo jo's pasta
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add garlic.
Cook briefly.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 1 minute.
Add wine, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Cook 10 minutes.
Heat 3 tablespoons of oil.
Add shrimp.
Cook 1 minute and add red pepper flakes.

title: pineapple-marshmallow sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Use more milk or fruit juice if needed.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake until heated through.
Remove from oven and cover top with marshmallows.
Return to oven and brown on top.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, mix dry ingredients (sugar, cocoa, flour and salt).
Then add milk and water.
Stir over low heat until it comes to a boil; stir constantly.
Add vanilla after removing from heat.

title: great chili(for cold days)
directions: Cook beef and onion, salt and pepper in large pot.
When fully cooked, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until good mixture of seasoning.
Beans are really good in this.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Add one egg at a time and beat thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients together and add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add flavorings and beat well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan. Cook 1 hour and 10 minutes at 275° or 300°.
Cool 15 minutes and turn on rack to cool.

title: low calorie, low-fat lemon oregano chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Make sure chicken is coated with marinade.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour, not longer. Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange chicken on a glass baking dish and pour the marinade on top.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings. Calories:
Fat points: 5.
Cholesterol:
66 mg.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken and brown. Add soup, water and vegetables. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serves 4.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing.
Use half of dressing when mixing and refrigerate.
Stir in remaining dressing before serving.

title: cola pot roast
directions: Brown all sides of roast in hot oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste and onions and carrots.
Stir in cola, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Add enough water to mixture to cover approximately 2/3's of the roast with liquid.
Cover pot and place in a 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Thicken liquid with cornstarch and water mixture.
Serve with hot mashed potatoes or extra wide egg noodles.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, lemon and orange juice.
Let stand at room temperature, 3 to 4 hours.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer; add whipping cream, milk and evaporated milk.
Freeze. Yield:
1 gallon.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until done.
Mix Ranch dressing into cream cheese.
Spread over baked crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables and press slightly.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat whites and salt until foamy; then add cream of tartar and finish mixing until stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar and mix well.
Then add cake flour and sugar mixture until thoroughly mixed.
Heat oven at 200° until you put cake in, then turn up to 350° and let bake about 1 hour.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Hull berries; set aside.
Mix pudding mix, sour cream and milk.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Beat with a wire whisk until blended.
Spoon half of mixture into crust and arrange berries, stem down.
Top with remaining filling.
Chill and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: tossed green beans
directions: Put beans and 1/4 cup water in casserole; cover.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes; drain well.

title: in-a-hurry ham casserole
directions: Drain and rinse noodles.
Place in lightly buttered casserole. Add ham to noodles.
Toss, breaking ham into fine chunks.
Pour mushroom soup and sour cream into noodle-ham mixture.
Mix well with wooden spoon.
Add fresh mushrooms.
Stir in celery salt and seasoned salt.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix chili sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard together and add ham.
Place in skillet and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 sandwiches.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; slice thinly.
Heat margarine in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Arrange potatoes in greased 2 quart casserole, in 3 layers, topping each layer with onion and sauce.
Cover and cook in 325° oven for 40 minutes. Uncover and cook 60 to 70 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Blend salad dressing, eggs, milk, broth, salt and soup. Pour over
layers
of
chicken, bread and cheese in crock-pot. Put crock-pot on high for 3 hours.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup, broccoli, cheese and mushrooms.
When hot, serve with Triscuits in chafing dish.
Can be frozen.

title: beef tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Remove grease.
Add onion.
Salt and pepper to suit taste.
Put cream of chicken soup in bottom of baking dish. Add 1/2 cup water.
Add meat and onions.
Pour mushroom soup over meat and onions.
Add cheese, then spread frozen Tater Tots over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and milk in heavy pan and cook until tender.
In bowl, beat egg yolks; slowly add the 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until light and lemon colored.
Add yolk mixture to rice; beat vigorously.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch glass pan and let cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add pinch of cream of tartar, then slowly add the 3 tablespoons of sugar on high speed until soft peaks form.
Spread on cooled rice. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes, until light brown.
Cool.

title: potato salad stuffed tomatoes
directions: Scoop out tomatoes; turn upside on a paper towel to drain. Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain, cool and cut into small cubes.
Place in medium size bowl.
Blend sour cream, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt, sugar, mustard, pepper and garlic in a small bowl.
Add green pepper and pimento to potatoes; toss with dressing.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Sprinkle remaining salt into tomato shells.
Spoon 2 tablespoons potato salad mixture into each tomato half.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl; add pineapple and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble crackers over top; pour butter evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese softened at room temperature.
Chop onions and meat.
Mix all together.
Shape into ball and chill.
Serve with crackers.
Roll ball in chopped nuts, usually about 1 cup.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in sour milk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add pecans, cherries and dates. Chill for one hour or overnight.
Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until set.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in large pot.
Cover with boiling water. When water returns to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove ribs from pot and place on baking pans.
Salt and pepper ribs to taste, then oil ribs lightly and brown both sides under broiler.
Place ribs flat in roasting pans and cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Baste and turn ribs every 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon basil chicken
directions: Combine oil and next 7 ingredients in shallow baking dish. Add chicken, turning once to coat both sides. Refrigerate for 30 - 45 minutes, turning once.
Pan braise on top of stove. Simmer till done. Green peppers and onions can be added to the chicken while it is frying.

title: diabetic cherry upside-down cake
directions: Drain
cherries.
Do
not use this liquid for reconstituting cake
since
it
would
discolor
the
cake.
Arrange cherries
in lightly greased and wax paper lined 8-inch round pan.
Mix
cake mix and half the water for 3 minutes in mixer. Add	remaining water
and	mix
1	minute.
Pour
batter over cherries.
Bake
at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.	Cool slightly. Loosen
cake around sides.
Invert onto serving plate.	Remove wax paper.
Makes one 8-inch cake, 10 servings at 112 calories per serving.

title: quaker and fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish. Combine all ingredients except preserves.
Mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup of oats mixture and press remaining into bottom of prepared dish.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spread preserves evenly over partially baked base to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Sprinkle reserved oats over mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together;
spoon into hot butter or margarine.
Fry until brown, 1 to 3 minutes on each side.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Split zucchini lengthwise and slice (about 3 to 3 1/2 cups).
Mix all ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium to high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot oil.
Cook half of the chicken until browned, stirring often. Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet in remaining oil, cook mushroom and onion until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in soup, yogurt and water.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs well.
Pour in small Corning Ware or bake dish.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top. Heat in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter snackers
directions: Mix together oats, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda in a large bowl.
In a medium bowl with a mixer, beat together oleo, peanut butter and two sugars, until light and fluffy, about 4 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat 1 minute after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix in oat mixture on low speed until blended.
Add chips or raisins.
Can chill the dough for 24 hours. Preheat oven to 350°.
Use tablespoon of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes, until golden or firm on edges.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil the potato until done.
Cool completely; peel and mash potato.
In another bowl, add a little of the potato and sugar alternating.
Put in a little sugar to the side.
Continue mixing potato and sugar until it becomes thick like a pie crust. Sprinkle remaining sugar on a dough board; roll out the potato and sugar mixture to about 1/2-thick thick.

title: eggplant-tomato casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crumbly; remove.
Saute pepper and onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add eggplant and tomato, cook 5 minutes.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbled bacon, cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise.
Remove egg yolks.
Mash with fork.
Add remaining ingredients to egg yolks; mix until smooth.
Take teaspoon of egg yolk and place in egg.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Stir in the rice and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and let it sit for about 15 minutes. In a large skillet, heat the oil.
Add the egg and cook until set, like scrambling eggs.
Add the meat.
Add rice, pepper and any desired vegetables such as green onion, bean sprouts, etc.
Stir to blend ingredients.
Add soy sauce and keep stirring until heated.

title: butterscotch chip torte
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together. Mix dates, water and soda. Cool. Cream oleo and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Add dry ingredients alternating with date mixture. Add vanilla. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle nuts and chips on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 12. Can freeze. Must do ahead.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Bring to a boil chicken, chicken broth, chicken soup and salsa.
Layer like lasagna, 3 layers high, using tortillas.
Put cheese on bottom and top layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Freeze solid in quart containers.
Just before serving, thaw enough to mash with potato masher.
Place in punch bowl.
Add 4 quarts ginger ale.
Makes enough for 40 servings.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and apples.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and apples.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue beef cups
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add garlic.
Add barbecue sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Press biscuits into ungreased muffin tins, covering sides and bottoms.
Fill each with barbecue mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° (or until golden brown).
Makes 10.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of greased crock-pot.
Wrap each piece of chicken with a strip of bacon and lay on tops of dried beef.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter for crust.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Put onions in a heavy skillet.
Add enough water to just cover them.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 15 minutes or until onions are transparent.
Drain well.
Put into crust.
Stir eggs into milk; pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.
It may be baked ahead of time and re-warmed.

title: nita hadsell's chicken and noodle soup
directions: Simmer ingredients together until onion and celery are cooked. Drop in homemade noodles.
Add chunks of vegetarian chicken if desired.
Simmer until noodles are tender (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: party snacks
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Cool; spread on bread slices.
Freeze on cookie sheets
for 2 hours.
Remove from cookie sheets and place in plastic bags.
Keep frozen until ready to use.
To serve, place on cookie sheets and heat in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: new banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk together and add sour cream and vanilla. Stir in Cool Whip.
Use a spoon or spatula for this.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Then spread filling over these. Continue layer after layer until all filling is used.

title: wickedly rich pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Add milk, coconut, eggs and sugar until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put leftovers in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, salt, milk and egg yolks in a saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cool 10 minutes and add vanilla. Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: low calorie chocolate pie
directions: Heat
chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in saucepan over very low
heat,	stirring
until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat; beat in cream cheese and remaining milk until well blended. Fold
in
whipped
topping,
blending
until smooth. Spoon	into crust.
Freeze
until firm, about 4 hours.	Cover and store any leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill mixture for 1 hour or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and roll into small balls (approximately the size of walnuts).
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks,

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (start with a wooden spoon and finish with your hands).
Roll into balls.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Cover loosely with more waxed paper and place in refrigerator until firm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix carrots, celery, onion and pepper together.
In separate bowl mix oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, tomato soup, sugar, dry mustard and salt together.
After mixing, pour over carrots, celery, onion and pepper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pastry crust mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening with knife or pastry blender until mixture is of pebbly consistency.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: rocky road pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl. Add instant pudding. Beat with wire whisk until well blended (about 1 minute). Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip, chocolate chips, nuts and marshmallows. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, at least 6 hours or overnight. Let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Then add flour and soda with buttermilk alternately.
Add spices, then apple juice concentrate, pecans and dried fruit.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes, then 5 minutes at 275°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown round steak in hot oil.
Put into baking pan.
Cover with sliced carrots, celery, onion, stewed tomatoes.
Cover with foil making a few holes for steam to escape.
Bake at 350 degrees for 2 hours.
Remove foil, cover with grated cheddar cheese and place in oven till cheese melts.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and two sugars until light. Stir in egg and applesauce.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to mixture; beat until smooth.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets and bake for 5 to 7 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Crem margarine or butter Crisco with eggs and Sweet 'N Low. Add remaining ingredients.
Add milk until consistency that can be dropped by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 23 minutes or until brown.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Add dressing to oil; pour over crackers in large bowl.
Stir with spatula until well mixed.

title: chocolate kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first six ingredients in mixing bowl and blend well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 9 1/2-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Combine 6 tablespoons Kahlua and confectioners sugar.
While cake is still warm in pan, poke holes in cake.
Pour liqueur mixture over.
Allow cake to cool in pan at least 2 hours before removing.

title: avocado cream cheese spread
directions: Peel avocado; mash pulp. Combine remaining ingredients. Add avocado. Cover; chill. Serve with seeded crackers. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Dice bacon; fry.
Take bacon out of grease.
Cook onion, green pepper and celery in bacon grease until tender.
Remove from grease and put in casserole dish with bacon.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix into casserole dish; add cheese.
Add about 1/3 tall can of tomato juice.
Mix; cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Remove lid; bake until brown around edges.

title: wild violet jam
directions: Rinse violet blossoms well.
Place in blender.
Add 3/4 cup water and lime juice.
Blend well.
Gradually add sugar, blending until a smooth paste is formed in a saucepan.
Combine pectin and remaining water.
Bring to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Add to blender and blend for 1 minute.
Quickly pour into prepared jars or glasses and seal.
Makes about 4 or 5 glasses.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place
drained	mixed vegetables in bottom of casserole dish. Mix mayonnaise, celery, onion and cheese and place over mixed vegetables.
Top
with
mixture
of
crumbs and butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good stuff!

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Boil celery, carrot and onion in broth until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Mix flour and butter; stir into broth.
Cook and stir until thickened; boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat; add beer and cheese.
Mix until smooth and cheese melts.
Heat just to serving temperature.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large saucepan, combine the chicken, 1/2 cup milk, soup and sour cream; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove the mixture from the heat and spoon it into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In a large bowl, heat the remaining 3/4 cup milk, the biscuit baking mix, cornmeal and butter.
Pour the mixture evenly over the hot chicken mixture and sprinkle the top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes, or until the top is set and the soup mixture bubbles around the edges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pork chop and stuffing bake
directions: Combine bread cubes, onion, celery, salt, poultry seasoning and water in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix to combine.
Arrange pork chops over stuffing.
Spoon soup over chops.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 25 to 30 minutes or until chops are tender, turning the dish once.

title: parmesan cheese toast
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices if desired.
Cut the bread slices if desired.
Cut the bread slices into quarters or bite size shapes using small cookie cutters.
Mix the mayonnaise, scallions, Parmesan cheese and pepper in a small bowl.
Spread over the bread slices.
Place on a baking sheet.
Broil until the cheese mixture turns golden brown and bubbly.
Watch carefully; do not burn.

title: surprise bread
directions: Let bread dough thaw completely.
Brown sausage and ground beef, with onion included.
Drain excess grease.
In large bowl, mix meat mixture, taco seasoning and corn.
Roll out bread dough; place one-third of cheese down center of each portion of dough. Place one-third meat mixture over cheese.
Fold ends of dough over; overlap sides to form loaf.
Gently press edges of dough together to seal.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Spread butter over each loaf.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Slice and serve with salad, and you have a complete meal.
Great party food, also.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla.
Save 1/2 cup batter to add to icing.
Bake in a lightly greased tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: kiwi fruit antipasto salad
directions: Peel kiwi fruit and slice into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Slice tomatoes and Mozzarella into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In small bowl, toss tomatoes with balsamic vinegar.
Divide kiwi, tomatoes and Mozzarella in 4 portions and arrange on 4 salad plates. Garnish with basil leaves and drizzle with olive oil.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Pour the hot dressing over the vegetables.
Cover lightly and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Makes 15 servings. Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
Great accent for summer meals.

title: steak meat balls
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, egg, milk and seasonings.
Mix well. Melt shortening in skillet; drop meat mixture by spoonfuls into shortening.
Brown on both sides.
Place in a covered buttered baking dish.
Blend 1/2 can water with soup and pour over meat balls.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: knock you naked cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk over cake.
Pour caramel topping over condensed milk.
Sprinkle half of Heath bars over this.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle rest of Heath bars over Cool Whip.

title: strawberry cheese delight
directions: Make a crust with coconut, oleo, sugar and flour.
Blend together and press into the bottom of 9-inch round pan or 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Chill.
Spread on half of the strawberry preserves.

title: shrimp a la creole
directions: Split shrimp and season with salt, black pepper and cayenne. Set aside.
Heat oil in heavy pot and cook onions and celery until wilted.
Add tomato sauce and paste and water.
Cook about 40 minutes or until oil comes to the top.
Add shrimp, bell pepper, garlic, sugar, salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Cook 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Boil chicken and take off bones.
Cut in pieces.
Add cream cheese and 1/2 of melted butter.
Put mixture in crescent rolls and roll up, being sure to fold in the ends and sides.
Roll in bread crumbs mixed in 1/2 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use broth from boiled chicken or cream of chicken soup for gravy for the top of the Chicken Bundles.

title: lobster dip
directions: Melt margarine and gradually stir in cheese. Break lobster into pieces. Stir in wine and lobster.
Heat thoroughly and serve with chips or crackers.

title: glorified cornflakes
directions: In a saucepan, mix together and cook the oleo, sugar, Karo and peanut butter.
When mixture comes to a hard boil, cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the cornflakes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: chicken with herbed rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil; set aside.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper. In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken and brown over medium-high heat.
Set aside.

title: sweet 'n sour salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, celery seed, mustard, salt and onion.
Add in small amounts of salad oil and cider vinegar, alternately to dry ingredients, ending with oil.
Shake vigorously.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Put ice cream on one graham crackers; put the other graham cracker on top of the ice cream.
Leave in freezer 2 to 4 days.

title: honey doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening.
Continue creaming while adding honey in a fine stream.
Add egg, baking powder, salt and milk; mix well. Add enough flour to roll out dough and cut easily.
Fry in deep hot fat.
The honey will keep these delicious doughnuts moist longer than usual.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid; add water to reserved liquid to equal 2 cups.
In a saucepan, bring beets and liquid to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add cold water, onions, horseradish, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in beets, celery and olives.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Cut salad in squares.
Add dollop of mayonnaise
and top with olives. Yields 9 to 12.

title: peared up
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt butter in baking dish and spread along bottom of dish.
Peel, quarter and pare pears.
Place pears cut side down on buttered baking dish.
Mix Karo and brandy in separate bowl and pour over pears.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve hot over vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill overnight.

title: sweet and sour glazed carrots
directions: Boil carrots with a little salt until tender, drain.
In a small saucepan over low heat, blend oleo and brown sugar, ginger and lemon juice until sugar melts.
Toss carrots gently until coated in this mixture and serve hot.
Makes six servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil 1 cup water. Remove from heat and add coffee. Stir until completely dissolved. Pour coffee mixture into 6-quart saucepan/stockpot. Add 6 cups warm, warm water and the 7 cups sugar. Stir slowly to dissolve sugar. If necessary, move stockpot to stove and turn heat to simmer/low. Leave on heat only long enough to dissolve sugar. Remove from heat once sugar is dissolved and cool. Mixture must be thoroughly cooled before proceeding. When completely cooled, add brandy/vodka and vanilla. Stir gently, but ensure vanilla and alcohol are thoroughly mixed/blended. Pour into clean, dry glass containers with screw lids. Do not fill bottles completely; leave 2-inches clear. Screw on lids, but leave loose. Store in dark, cool dry space for 4 days. On fifth day, tighten lids and store normally. Makes 4 to 5 fifths.

title: one-two-three-four cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and mix with butter and sugar.
Sift flour and mix with baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter and add vanilla.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Remove stems and tear into bite size pieces.
Store in a plastic bag until serving.

title: ole cowboy chili
directions: Mix all spices together.
Spray large skillet with Pam.
Brown beef, onion and garlic together.
Sprinkle with cornstarch.
Empty beef mixture into a Dutch oven pan.
Add tomato paste and stir in spice mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Turn burner to medium heat and stir in water.
Leave chili as thick as desired. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low simmer.
Let simmer until spices are cooked, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Add more water for right thickness.
Stir occasionally.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine first five ingredients in covered jar and shake well. Keep in refrigerator.
Shred cabbage.
Small amounts of carrots, onions or onion flakes are optional.
Mix dressing with cabbage. Chill.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients, whisking well to incorporate sugar.
Use marinade on any meat.
Brush on steaks while grilling and right before serving.

title: chocolate pies (2)
directions: Cook pie shells first (use directions on package). Beat egg yolks, then add sugar and beat together. In separate bowl, sift flour and cocoa together. Add to egg mixture and mix, then add hot water and mix together, then add milk and mix. Put in 2-quart pot and cook on medium heat, stirring constantly. When mixture starts to thicken, add butter and vanilla flavor. Continue to stir until thick. Pour into precooked shells and let pies cool completely.

title: easy drop dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add milk.
Stir until just mixed.

title: tomatoes au gratin
directions: Saute onion in butter in skillet until tender.
Combine cheese and crumbs in bowl; mix well.
Layer half the tomatoes, onion and cheese crumbs in 6 x 11-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Combine remaining ingredients except parsley, in bowl; mix well.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: polka daters
directions: Mix dates and hot water and set aside to cool. Beat butter, sugar and eggs until creamy. Stir in gradually the flour and baking soda. Add the date mixture (water and dates) and vanilla, mixing thoroughly. Add all the chocolate chips or you can reserve some to sprinkle on top after batter is in the pan. Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Top with reserved chocolate chips and nuts (optional). Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, let sit overnight in refrigerator. Soften tortillas by placing in microwave for 1 minute while still in package.

title: nothings
directions: Mix well.
Pour in 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or little more if necessary.
Check middle to see if cooked through.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: zesty chicken
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, pepper, garlic, lemon zest, lemon juice and sliced peppers in a mixing bowl.
Add chicken and combine well.
Marinate for 1 hour, stirring mixture after 1/2 hour.
Saute in large skillet for 10 minutes on medium-high, covered, until chicken is just done.
Spoon chicken and sauce over a bed of risotto or egg noodles to serve.

title: plum kuchen
directions: In bowl, stir flour, 1/4 cup sugar and salt together.
Cut in butter until mixture is the consistency of cornmeal.
Pack into ungreased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches), pressing against bottom and sides.
Arrange pricked plum halves, skin side up, in rows on top. In bowl combine 3/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over fruit.
Bake in quick 400° oven for 15 minutes.
In bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in heavy cream.
Remove kuchen from oven and pour cream mixture evenly over fruit.
Return to oven and continue baking for 30 minutes more.

title: quick and easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add pineapple, egg and vanilla. Mix well.
Bake
in
greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan for approximately 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: unbelievable chocolate fudge brownies
directions: Melt butter (or margarine) and chocolate cubes together slowly in pan or in a covered double boiler.
In bowl, put flour and sugar and mix well.
Pour melted butter and chocolate into flour mixture. Stir.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat by hand for 3 minutes. Add package of chocolate chips; mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes only.
Remove from oven and cool.
Do not overbake.
Will be almost like fudge when cool. For real chocolate lovers only.

title: mickey's mystery meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients, except bacon.
Form into a loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Cut bacon strips in half. Lay over top of the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Mix together cauliflower, onion, green pepper, bacon and cheese.
Add mayonnaise mixture and refrigerate.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Dredge chicken breasts in seasoned flour and brown in oil.
Place chicken in casserole with mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Stir garlic and spices with tomatoes and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender, adding sherry during the last few minutes of cooking time.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Toss stuffing mix in melted margarine.
Place half in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine other ingredients and spoon into dish. Top with rest of stuffing.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Can use any kind of squash.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix together at least 12 hours before serving. Excellent on all kinds of crackers.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.
(May omit flattening with fork and press chocolate candy kiss in center of each cookie after baking.)

title: diabetic (sugarless) banana walnut cake
directions: In a bowl, beat together bananas and oleo until creamy; add eggs and water.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking power, soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until when tested with toothpick, it comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Layer potatoes in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix ground beef with soup and string beans.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spread mixture over potatoes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zippy tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours or until thick.

title: carolyn's red velvet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream oil and eggs; add sugar.
Add food color, vanilla, white vinegar and buttermilk.
Mix.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 baking pans and bake for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion for about 6 to 7 minutes. Do not drain. Heat milk in microwave. Add to broccoli, along with salt and pepper. Simmer about 5 minutes. Add chicken and cheese. Simmer about 5 more minutes. May want to thicken with flour and water mixture.

title: mochi(sweet glutinous japanese rice cakes)
directions: Stir together rice, flour, salt and sugar. Stir in 1/2 cup water to form soft dough.

Lightly knead about 30 seconds on a surface dusted with katakuriko. Bring 4 cups water to a boil in deep pot. Spread a piece of dampened unbleached muslin or several layers of cheesecloth over a steamer tray. Spread dough evenly over dampened cloth, about 1/2-inch thick.

title: john's coconut crunchies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and vanilla.
Add egg and mix until smooth.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together and add to the creamed mixture.
Blend in rolled oats, cornflakes and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat and reserve for later. Crumble bacon.
In large bowl toss potatoes, bacon, onions and celery.
Combine enough water to cornstarch to make a smooth paste, set aside.
Heat remaining water in a pan, add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Next add 1 tablespoon bacon fat and pepper.
Bring to a boil before adding cornstarch mixture and stir sauce until it is clear.
Pour sauce over potato mixture.
Warm in microwave oven until heated through.

title: hopping john
directions: Rinse peas.
In a 3-quart saucepan, add peas to water ; cover and bring to boiling.
Boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat and let stand for 1 hour.
Add onion, pepper, red pepper, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling, cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring once or twice.
Stir in salt pork and simmer, uncovered, for 50 to 60 minutes more, until tender, stirring frequently.
Remove salt pork and bay leaf; mash the pea mixture slightly.
Season to taste with salt, if desired.
Serve with hot rice.

title: creamy chocolate bits
directions: Mix
with
fork
in bowl.
Then work mixture with hands until it forms a ball.
Dust board lightly with confectioners sugar. Knead
candy
mixture
about
20 times on board.
Then roll mixture into balls about the size of walnuts.
Roll each ball in chopped nuts or multi-colored candies.
Makes about 48 balls.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and Cheddar cheese come to room temperature. Mix cheeses gradually.
Add dressing mix a little at a time until entire package is used.
If too sticky, refrigerate or place in freezer 30 to 45 minutes.
Shape into ball or roll and roll in pecans.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl sift together first 7 ingredients.
Add salad oil, eggs, shredded carrots, crushed pineapple (with syrup) and vanilla.
Mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, butter, pecans and 2 ounces of Pet milk.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch aluminum pan.
Bake at 350°
for 8 minutes.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly.
Add coconut, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips in layers.
Pour milk over layers evenly.
Sprinkle nuts on top and gently press down.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: dinner rolls or sweet rolls or loaf bread
directions: Mix warm
water,
sugar
and yeast in mixer.
Let yeast begin to dissolve,
then	add eggs, shortening and add 1 quart of flour; mix until smooth.
Add rest of flour, one quart at a time.	Knead dough
until
satiny smooth.
Oil down and put in pan until doubled
in
bulk,	1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and cut into rolls or loaf;
let
rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake in oven
at
350° for one hour.
Bread will sound hollow when thumped.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, hot water, sugar, orange and lemon juice.
Cool. When ready to serve, add 7-Up and sherbet.
Serves 35.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan.
Add onions, celery and bell peppers.
Cook for 10 minutes, until onions are clear.
Add flour; blend in well.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add parsley and crawfish tails.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add cream, cheese and garlic; mix well. Add salt and pepper (I use Tony Chachere, too).
Cook, covered, on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and add sauce mixture; mix thoroughly.
Pour into 3 lightly buttered casserole dishes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
(You can use 1 pound crawfish and 1/3 recipe for smaller amount.)

title: mushroom butter
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon butter in skillet and saute mushrooms for 3 minutes. Remove and mince. Add the rest of the butter, salt and nutmeg. If you have a food processor, process until a smooth paste. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: speedy potato chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon bacon drippings.
In hot drippings, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and milk until well mixed.
Add vegetables with its liquid, "meat", parsley and reserved bacon.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
