Makes about 4 cups/4 servings.

title: honeymooners' salad
directions: Mix ingredients in bottom of salad bowl.
(This is strictly to taste, so add as much or as little as you want.)
Add cut up lettuce and toss.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, poppy seed and soda.
In large bowl cream together sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs, then yogurt and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: taco potatoes
directions: Cook beef in microwave for 3 minutes.
Let stand (set) for 1 minute.
Pour off grease.
Add taco seasoning mix and 1/2 amount of water required on the package.
Add beans and cook in microwave for 1 minute.
Open potatoes; spoon on beef mixture.
Add lettuce, tomato, onion, cheese and sour cream.
Freeze any left over beef mixture for taco salad or another potato meal.

title: layered english pea salad
directions: Layer the first five ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and sweetener or sugar.
Cover salad to edges.
Continue layering with egg wedges and grated cheese.
Let set overnight.
Add bacon bits before serving.

title: chicken minestrone soup
directions: In soup pot, saute chicken in oil.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and set aside.
Saute garlic and onion in remaining oil. Add celery, zucchini, tomatoes with juice, chicken broth, water, herbs, spices, chicken and beans.
Simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes.
Add pasta and simmer for 15 more minutes.
Taste and add additional seasoning, if desired.
Serve topped with grated cheese and parsley or basil.
Lots of ingredients, but worth it.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done.
Drain.
Add ingredients of margarine, Velveeta (shredded), 2 eggs, 1 1/2 cups dressing and 2 finely chopped jalapenos to squash in casserole dish.
Top with more cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Chop onion; grate carrots.
Chop celery; chop green pepper.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple well and use juice with the following.
Beat egg; add sugar, flour and vinegar.
Slowly add juice and cook until thick.
Cool.
The dressing should be real thick.
Add the pineapple and cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas with spicy sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in the sour cream and chopped peppers.
Pour half of the sour cream sauce into a lightly greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside dish and remaining sauce.
Fry the tortillas, one at a time, in 2 tablespoons of oil for 5 seconds on each side or until softened.
Place 1 tablespoon each of chicken, cheese and onions on each tortilla and roll up. Pour remaining sauce over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more.
Garnish with Spicy Sauce.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and cook potatoes until done.
In saucepan, mix soups, milk and butter.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Put potatoes in crock-pot and pour mixture over potatoes.
Stir.
Lay Velveeta cheese on top.
Cook for about 1 hour.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Cool, peel and grate using largest hole in grater.
Heat butter and cheese until almost melted. Remove and blend in sour cream.
Fold in potatoes.
Put in 2-quart greased casserole.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini blondies
directions: Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with Pam.
Line bottom with wax paper.
Spray paper.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Beat together the butter and sugar in a medium size bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat lightly.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dressing and water; mix well until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured pan 25 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy snack mix
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Add seasoned salt, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cereals and nuts; mix well.
Stir in butter mixture; stir until well blended.
Spread into two 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
(Yield:
20 cups.)

title: rabbit ragout with grit dumplings
directions: Saute the onion in hot oil.
Add the diced meat, saute briefly and then add the carrot, celery, salt and pepper.
Saute together for 10 minutes.
Pour over the soup stock and cook for about 30 minutes.

title: oyster patties
directions: Purchase 12 patties from
the bakery and cut center top out to set aside.	Carefully cut circle in top to remove.

title: light rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over Crisco, sugar and salt and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Beat eggs until creamy.
Mix yeast, eggs and water.
Stiffen with flour and knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down once.
Pan into rolls and let double in size.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and other ingredients together with the juice of the lemon; fold in the Cool Whip last.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.

title: tuna-rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Put in eggs and mix up with fork. Add rice, milk, tuna and salt; mix all together.
Place cheese slices over the top.
Bake 25 minutes in a 325° oven.
Makes eight servings.

title: superb potato casserole
directions: Heat soup, cheese, chives, 1/4 pound margarine and sour cream in saucepan until cheese melts.
Fold into potatoes.
In small pan, combine and saute cornflake crumbs in margarine.
Put potato mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good served with ham which can be added to this casserole.

title: oatmeal-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes until top and crust is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole(serves 6 to 8.)
directions: Mix all together; place in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut recipe in 1/2 for 3 to 4 servings.

title: black cherry jello mold
directions: Mix jello and boiling water together until dissolved.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Chill slightly, then spread sour cream and powdered sugar mixture on top.
Chill until firm.

title: pie crust(enough for 2 crust pie)
directions: Mix Crisco with flour, sugar and salt with hands until like corn meal.
Spread between waxed paper and roll out thin.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry lime sorbet
directions: In blender combine strawberries and their syrup, 1/2 cup of water, lime juice and sugar; blend well.
Pour into 8-inch square baking pan; freeze about 1 1/2 hours.
Transfer mixture to small bowl.
With electric mixer at medium speed, beat until slushy. Return to freezer, freeze until firm.
Place in refrigerator 1 hour before serving to soften.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 1/2 hour.
Melt lard in boiling water; let cool.
Sift flour, salt and sugar into a large bowl.
Make a well in center in which to pour the dissolved yeast, melted lard and water.
Add last beaten eggs; beat and mix well.
Let rise 1 hour in warm place.
Knead a little and make out into rolls.
Put in a warm place to rise; let rise until double in size.
It takes about 2 hours.
Bake in a moderate oven (370°) until golden brown.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Make bread crumbs in blender.
Add onion, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, 1 teaspoon dry mustard and 1/2 can tomato sauce to ground beef.
Mix together and make a loaf. Put in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cover with sauce.

title: cheese and egg dish
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Cut white bread into 1-inch squares. Fry bacon crisp.
Crumble.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish:
bread, cheese, bacon, cheese, bread, etc.
Beat eggs, add cream (do not whip) and salt.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator about 30 minutes before cooking.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.

title: coconut frosting tinted pink
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler.
Beat until thoroughly mixed, then place over rapidly boiling water, beating constantly and cook for 18 minutes or until frosting will stand in peaks.
Add coloring to hot frosting to give delicate shell pink tint.
Remove from boiling water, add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes enough frosting for 3 layer cake and 1 extra cup for decorating.

title: rhubarb cherry dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine and set aside the rhubarb, 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cherry pie filling and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain excess water.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Top with eggs.
Add tomatoes.
Add cheese soup.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and oregano.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Mix Cajun seasoning, Parmesan cheese and crushed corn flakes. Wash chicken breasts and pat dry. Spread with mayonnaise and roll in corn flakes mixture.

title: crock-pot reubens
directions: Drain and dry sauerkraut.
Place in bottom of slow cooker. Add corned beef.
Top with cheese.
Cover and cook on low 3 to 4 hours.
Serve on toasted rye bread with sandwich spread.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix sour cream, water and eggs.
Stir in cake mix (batter will be lumpy).
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour glaze ham
directions: Combine apple juice, mustard, lemon juice and ground cloves in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Set aside.

title: cowpuncher stroganoff
directions: Place ground beef and onion in a 2-quart glass casserole dish, mixing well.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring once.
Add the next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Microwave on Medium for 7 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Microwave on Medium for 4 minutes. Serve over noodles.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 36 muffin cups with oil or paper cups. Lightly spoon flour into cups.
In big bowl, combine flour, wheat flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisins and walnuts or pecans; mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs; stir until just moistened.
Fill muffin cup 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately remove from pans.

title: dutch pancake
directions: You also need an iron skillet, No. 10.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place a layer of bread slices in dish.
Layer cheese, vegetables
and meat on top of bread.
Cover with another layer of bread.
Combine milk, eggs, onion, salt and mustard.
Pour over the layered food in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes. Can sprinkle more cheese on top during the last 5 minutes of baking.
Let sit 10 minutes before slicing.

title: fastnachts
directions: Sieve potatoes to make them smooth.
Save water from cooking potatoes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar. Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Cream together potatoes, sugar, salt and margarine.
Beat in eggs and add warm liquids.
Add flour gradually, kneading dough until it is soft, but not sticky.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Punch down and roll with rolling pin.
Cut
out with doughnut cutter or floured drinking glass.
Let rise again until double.
Place 3 to 4 doughnuts in shortening heated to 350° to 375°, turning once to fry second side.
Place on paper towel or brown paper.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Sift flour, spices and sugar together.
Mix soda into pulp and lemon juice (be careful, this will foam up, use large bowl!).
Add pulp to dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts, dates and raisins. Mix well.
Pour into well oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until moistened.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: brazilian peanut pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, blend eggs, milk and condensed milk over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
In an 11 3/4 x 9 1/4-inch pan, layer tea biscuits (dipped in half and half), milk mixture and ground peanuts, repeating layers 3 times, ending with peanuts.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: orange-marshmallow-rice confetti
directions: Combine oranges and marshmallows in large bowl.
Refrigerate 2 hours; drain if necessary.
Add cooked rice and walnuts.
Fold in Dream Whip gently; refrigerate 1 hour longer.
Stir mixture; lightly pile into compote.
If desired, garnish with unpeeled, halved thin orange slices.
Yields 12 servings.

title: my old kentucky home jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix spices, soda and flour. Add dry ingredients, alternately with milk.
Add jam.
Bake at 350°.

title: wisconsin strata
directions: Spread bread with a mixture of melted butter and mustard.
Put one slice of ham and Swiss cheese between bread slices.
Cut each sandwich crosswise into 4 triangles.
Line up sandwiches, pointed side up, in an 8-cup shallow casserole.
Beat eggs with wire whip in bowl until well blended.
Add milk.
Pour evenly over sandwiches, coating bread thoroughly.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Remove plastic wrap and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill hot dog rolls with mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake for 30 minutes at 250°.
Makes good luncheon entree.

title: buttery oatmeal crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a cookie sheet with foil or parchment paper and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine oats, sugar, flour, and baking powder; set aside.

title: strawberry pudding cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Cool and remove from pan.
Thaw berries.
Prepare pudding mix according to directions. Mix most of berries into pudding (save some for garnish) and spread on cake.
Whip the cream with the sugar.
Spread on pudding.
Garnish with remaining berries.
Chill well.

title: western pot roast
directions: In heavy pot, brown all sides of beef roast in oil.
Add onion and cook until golden.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 3 hours. Serve with carrots and potato chunks.
Serves 8.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and half can of coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Chill.
Top with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: christmas noodles
directions: Cook 2 large bags of noodles in juices from ham and turkey, two cans of chicken broth and four soup cans of water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: shortening bread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Gradually add flour. Roll out 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut as desired. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° until light brown.
Do not overcook.
Do not freeze.
They will keep for weeks in an airtight container.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Line pan with crescent rolls. Pour cheese mixture into pan and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until light brown.
Turn off oven; leave cake in oven, with door slightly open, about 1 hour, until cracked.

title: mama's coconut cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually. Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes. (She beat her batter by hand). Sift dry ingredients. Add eggs one at a time to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition. Add flour mixture with milk, almond, and vanilla extracts. Pour into 3 greased 9 inch pans. Line bottom of pans with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks.

title: apple stuffing for fish
directions: Fry salt pork until crisp, remove salt pork from skillet. Cook celery, onion and parsley in pan with fat from salt pork until tender.
Add diced apples, sprinkle with sugar, cover and cook until juice evaporates and apples are candied.
Add other ingredients and finish cooking.
Stuff your fish, season with salt and pepper and lemon juice to taste.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust and fill with apples. Mix flour, sugar and cloves together. Add sour cream and mix. Pour over apples, sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top.

title: oven tuna(a ladies luncheon treat!)
directions: Combine and pile lightly into individual baking dishes or a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese (or Cheddar).
Bake until bubbly in a 425° oven (about 10 to 15 minutes).
This is a great way to use the end of the box corn flakes that nobody wants to finish up.

title: blitz torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Cream the butter. Add sugar with the 4 egg yolks, one at a time. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add to butter mixture alternating with the 5 tablespoons milk. Spread into paper lined, greased round cake pans.
Beat 4 egg whites very stiff and add 1 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread meringue on top of each cake pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Keep checking after 30 minutes.
Cool. Remove from pans and take paper off. Beat cream, milk and pudding together.
Place one layer upside down and spread with pudding.
Place second layer meringue side up on top. Can add fresh strawberries (cut up) or raspberries in middle.

title: quick apple streudel
directions: Prepare crust for streudel by first dissolving the butter in boiling water.
Cool.
Blend in 1 slightly beaten egg yolk and flour, sifted with salt.
Beat until very smooth.
Now let pastry stand while preparing the filling.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with celery, onion and bell pepper. Drain excess fat. Add tomato sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell and freeze.
Drizzle hot fudge on each serving (optional).

title: taco pie for 2
directions: Thaw pie crusts for 10 minutes.
Heat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Bake crusts for 10 minutes (be sure to poke holes in crusts).

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt Crisco; remove from heat.
Blend in sugar, corn syrup and eggs.
Stir in pecan halves.
Bake for 50 minutes or until set; cool.

title: pheasant and dressing
directions: I don't have
a
recipe for pheasant and dressing, so I recently fixed
my	recipe	for
dressing and just substituted pheasant
for
the chicken, it turned out well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery until clear.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party pumpkin pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry.
Combine ice cream and candied ginger. Spread ice cream mixture in shell.
Freeze.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ground ginger and nutmeg.
Whip cream; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Add marshmallows.
Spread pumpkin mixture over ice cream layer.
Freeze.
Serve with additional whipped cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly; pack firmly into loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to package.
Drain and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add broccoli and cook until tender. Add other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.
(May cook in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High.)

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits, salt, water and milk until thick.
Add margarine and cheese.
Beat eggs and add to grits mixture.
Stir until cheese melts and no white grits show.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all the ingredients together. Pour into greased tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mark's corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake 30 minutes in iron skillet at 400°.

title: microwave broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli; set aside.
Put onion and butter into 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave for 4 minutes on High temperature; stir once.

title: chicken-broccoli chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and cheese in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; reduce heat. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in chicken and cheese.
Cover and cook until hot, about 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Heat milk slowly; add thinly sliced cheeses and stir constantly until smooth.
Add green onions and serve with nacho chips or Doritos.

title: yogurt-cucumber salad dressing
directions: Cucumber may be grated by hand or shredded with a food processor.
Drain cucumber in a colander.
Squeeze out excess liquid.
Remove and discard any large pieces of skin left behind by the food processor.

title: broccoli salad 1
directions: Mix together the above.

title: juicy hamburgers
directions: Form burgers and fry or grill as usual.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; stir into milk.
Add lemon juice and flavoring.
Pour into crumb crust.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in water for 7 minutes.
Add soup, 1/4 cup water, milk and cheeses.
Simmer until all cheese is melted.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion until tender.
Add taco seasoning; set aside.
Mix Ro-Tel, tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup together; set aside.
Layer in a large casserole dish, meat, Doritos, soup mixture, etc., ending with Doritos.
Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until cheese is bubbling.

title: almond joy balls
directions: Mix coconut, almonds, Eagle Brand milk and powdered sugar and make into balls.
Let set in fridge for 1 hour.
After the hour use a double boiler and melt household wax and chocolate chips. Then stick toothpicks in balls.
Dip in the chocolate and cool on wax paper.
Take toothpicks out.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind
peppers	together.
Mix	with sugar and vinegar. Cook 4 minutes.
Skim off top; cook 4 more minutes.
Let cool. Add Certo. Makes approximately 13 baby food jars.

title: whole wheat potato bread
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil unpeeled until VERY tender. Measure 3/4 cup of the potato water and pour into your bread mixing bowl. Dissolve the 1 teaspoon sugar into the lukewarm water and stir in dry yeast in another bowl. Let set. Break eggs into small bowl and beat lightly. Peel potatoes and mash in the 3/4 cup potato water. Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, the shortening and salt. Blend well. Add the dissolved yeast, then the 4 eggs. Blend thoroughly. Beat in the flour a little at a time. Dough will be stiff. Knead for 10 minutes. Cover and let rise 90 minutes until doubled. Grease 3 standard loaf pans. Punch dough down and knead again for 5 more minutes. Divide into 3 parts. Shape into loaves and let rise in pans for another hour.

title: broccoli a la ritz
directions: Cook broccoli in water per directions.
Drain.
Roll crackers into fine crumbs.
Melt 1/2 butter and add to crumbs.
Melt other half with Velveeta cheese.
Add this mixture to cooked broccoli. Put into greased casserole, alternating layers of crumbs and broccoli cheese mixture, ending with crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Should be nicely browned on top.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add brown sugar.
Put a layer of nuts, then a layer of pineapple (drained).
Make batter by mixing flour, eggs, sugar, baking powder, water and pineapple juice.
Pour into skillet and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Use heavy iron skillet.

title: yeast bread
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, salt and milk; bring to a boil, then let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to milk; gradually add flour.
Let rise to double.
Knead; cut with cutter.
Put in pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange float
directions: Mix and let set 2 hours.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve with grilled meats, tortillas, or chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread over chicken.
Add Stove Top stuffing.
Make as directed and spread on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.

title: sweet cucumber pickle rings
directions: Mix lime and first amount of water; pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash good in clear water.
Layer with ice and let stand overnight.
Drain.

title: kung pao pork
directions: Combine pork and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, lemon juice, sugar, cornstarch, crushed pepper and 1/4 cup water.
In wok or large skillet, stir-fry pork and garlic in hot oil 3 minutes or until brown.
Add bell pepper and onion; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add peanuts.

title: peanut butter pie(kids' delite)
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter until creamy.
Add warm milk, not hot and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into the graham cracker crusts.
Chill before serving.
This recipe freezes well.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and corn meal. Add the lemon rind, lemon juice, butter, eggs and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until top is golden brown and filling has puffed up all over.

title: egg souffle
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange bread in pan (with crusts already cut off).
In
large bowl, beat the eggs;
add remaining ingredients and
your
choice
of
meat.
Pour over bread. Bake in 350° oven for
40 to 50 minutes.
Dish can be made the night before.
Just cover and store in refrigerator.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Top with cheese, if desired, and bake for 10 minutes more.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter. Stir in crumbs. Pat firmly on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Chill. In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in condensed milk and undrained strawberries. Fold in marshmallows and whipping cream. Pour over crust in baking dish. Chill 2 hours, until set. If desired, garnish with whipped topping and fresh strawberries.

title: chestnut stuffing
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Moisten with butter, melted in the hot milk.
Chop the chestnuts fine and add to the bread crumbs mixture.
Mix thoroughly.

title: brownie iowa bars
directions: Beat margarine
and sugar well; add eggs, then mix rest of ingredients well. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cover with the mixed together sugar, butter, oatmeal, flour and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lightning microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in medium bowl. Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes or until margarine is melted. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch square pan. Cool. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
When cool, add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Set in refrigerator.
Mix pineapple juice, flour, sugar, butter and beaten egg.
Heat until thick.
Mix in softened cream cheese.
Let cool but not hard.
Beat 1 pint of whipped cream and fold into cooled mixture.
Top over the jello mixture that has been congealed.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion, then add the rest of the ingredients.

title: beef rinskoladin
directions: Spread each slice with mustard.
Sprinkle with cayenne powder/pepper, a few capers, salt and pepper and put small amounts of cut up uncooked bacon and julienned potatoes, onion and pickles in each.
Roll and secure with toothpick.

title: zesty get-up-an-go snack
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix first 4 ingredients together in long pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and drizzle over cereal mixture.
Toss until evenly coated.
Bake 10 minutes, stirring once.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 18 servings.

title: smoked venison
directions: *For 8 to 12 pounds of venison, use 10 to 15 pounds of charcoal, 7 quarts of water and cook 10 to 14 hours; for 13 to 30 pounds of venison, use 15 to 20 pounds of charcoal, 8 quarts of water and cook 14 to 16 hours.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Great for company!

title: quick and easy candy
directions: Melt oleo; add peanut butter, then powdered sugar.
Pour into buttered pan.
Place candy bars on top.
Bake at 200° for 5 minutes.

title: cabbage, cabbage and carrots
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients to the taste and stir until blended.
Refrigerate in covered bowl until crispy.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas in can.
Cut onion and put in peas.
Add soup (if needed).
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Add dressing of your choice until it sticks all together with butter.
Stir all together and put in refrigerator.
Does not need refrigeration if you eat it right away.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 over graham crackers; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Top with a layer of crackers.
Put chocolate syrup over top.
Chill overnight.

title: beef enchilada pie
directions: While meat is browning, cut tortillas into strips.
Mix all other ingredients.
When meat is brown, add to other mixture.
In a baking dish, place a layer of tortilla strips and a layer of the mixture, then another layer of tortilla strips and another layer of mixture.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread pie shell on pizza pan.
Glaze ingredients:
orange juice, lemon juice, water, cornstarch, sugar, and salt.
Mix ingredients together in a pan.
Bring to a boil and cook until clear, about 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, and 1/2 C. sugar until creamy.
Spread on crust.
Make sure fruit is well drained.
Dip bananas in lemon or pineapple juice so they won't turn brown.
Arrange fruit the way you want and put cooled glaze on top.
Good plain or with whipped cream.

title: shepherd pie casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and salt and pepper to taste.
Add peas and vinegar.

Add just enough Bisto (Canadian flavored cornstarch) or use regular cornstarch, just enough to make it stick together. Put mashed potatoes on top, flavored with butter, garlic salt and salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with crushed crackers.
Mix veggies, chestnuts, mayonnaise, onions and grated cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Top with cracker mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Chop up onion and pepper and put on top of meat.
Pour tomato sauce over the meat, onion and pepper.
Add the pinto beans.
Mix Jiffy corn bread mix and spread over the beans.
Put into oven and bake at 350° until done.

title: sausage skillet
directions: In skillet, brown kielbasa. While kielbasa is cooking, chop peppers and apple.
When Kielbasa is cooked, add peppers and apple.
Cook till peppers are just tender.
Serve with rice or pasta as a side dish.

title: carrot-bran muffins
directions: Mix six dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine all remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Gradually add dry ingredients to this mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Fill 18 greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple butter
directions: Add together in large roaster.
Place in oven at 350° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours or until thick, stirring frequently.
Then put in jars.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in a baking pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: butterfly lamb barbecue
directions: Marinate overnight.
Barbecue on hot coals 7 minutes per side or 25 to 30 minutes over all, basting as you do, or until done.

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add 3 cups flour, sifted with the salt and baking powder.
Mix remaining flour with cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Stir into batter and add vanilla. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir hamburger and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in soup.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: blue cheese slaw
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to make dressing.
Chill several hours (up to 24).
Toss with cabbage and Blue cheese at serving time. Serves 8.

title: texas two-step chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Mix picante sauce, sugar and mustard. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done. Serve over rice.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: For topping, set aside sour cream, 1/2 cup cheese and 2 cups Doritos.

title: syrian bread
directions: Sift 1/2 the flour; add sugar and salt and finish sifting flour.
Pastry blend in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in
1 cup warm water and knead in with about 5 more cups of water.
Keep dipping hands in warm water while kneading to get all flour mixed in well. Cover and let rise for 2 hours (past top of pan).
Break into pieces the size of a tangerine and roll out with flour 1/4-inch thick (size of a saucer).
Let rise 1 hour; bake for 5 minutes at 450° and rub with Crisco.

title: hearty chili soup
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat; cook garlic and onions for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mashing with fork.
Stir in tomatoes and one tomato can of water, celery, carrots, green pepper, chili powder, oregano, basil, hot pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Stir in chickpeas and 1 chick can of water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on individual servings.

title: one minute cookies
directions: Bring to a full boil in pan, sugar, oleo, milk and chips. Remove from heat and add oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: canned sweet pickles
directions: In a pan, place cucumbers and salt.
Cover with ice; let stand for 3 hours.
In a saucepan, bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: mock cheese souffle
directions: Mix together milk, eggs, salt, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, dry mustard and ground pepper grains.
Butter the casserole/souffle dish and, starting with bread, layer the bread and cheese.
Pour milk and mixture slowly over casserole.
Let stand for 1 hour or more.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and plums in bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: finger jello
directions: Add 1 cup cold water to 3 packages of gelatin.
Stir well. Suggest place in pot and cook very briefly over low heat on stove to dissolve gelatin thoroughly.

title: low-fat fried chicken
directions: Bone chicken breast, split and butterfly each piece or put between wax paper and hammer thin.
Spread each side of chicken with light covering of mayonnaise or dip in egg white.
Mix herbs (chopped, if fresh) with bread crumbs and roll chicken pieces until well covered.
Spray a nonstick wok or fryer with nonfat cooking spray.
Put on medium heat and add oil.
Fry chicken approximately 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Good topped with a little salsa for garnish.
Serves 2.

title: easy tuna
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat and serve on toast.

title: spice chiffon cake
directions: In a bowl, sift first 8 ingredients together.
(Spoon cake flour lightly-do not peak.)

title: fruit tea
directions: Make your tea using 10 to 12 family size tea bags in 5 quarts water.
Add other ingredients and serve.

title: the best potato soup
directions: Fill large pot half full with water. Add margarine, onion and potatoes. Boil for 15 minutes. Do not drain. Add remaining ingredients, seasoning to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix equal parts in blender.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven; add flour and cook, stirring constantly until mixture is browned (about 10 minutes).
Stir in onion and celery.
Cook over medium, about 5 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes with liquid, water, bay leaf, garlic, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add okra.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in file powder.
Remove bay leaf and serve in bowls over rice.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat 3 eggs, cooking oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Mix in separate bowl zucchini and crushed pineapple.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Mix together nuts and dates.
To flour mixture, add nuts and dates. Stir into liquid mixture, then stir in pineapple and zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Make sure to line the bottom of greased baking pan(s) with waxed paper.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and tear into small pieces.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then pour over crushed Ritz crackers.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on top. Cover with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken with lime butter
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
In large frying pan place oil and heat to medium temperature.
Add chicken and saute 4 minutes or until light brown.
Turn chicken, cover and reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Remove chicken and keep warm; drain off oil and discard.
In same fry pan, add lime juice and cook over low heat until juice begins to bubble.
Add butter, stirring until butter becomes opaque.
Stir in chives and dill weed.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roast beef and gravy(100 portions)
directions: Roast in oven at high temperature (450°) until brown.
Add 3 quarts water and the rest of the ingredients.
Then turn down oven to 300° and cover roaster.
May need to add water, if water is gone, during cooking.
Cook until done.
Take roast out of pan and cool 1/2 hour prior to slicing.
This will firm it up.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook in salted water to cover about 10 minutes.
Drain and use potato water in sauce.
In separate pan melt oleo.
Stir in flour, dry mustard and onion salt.
Add liquid and cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Layer potatoes and ham in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over and sprinkle with additional cheese if desired.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal chocolate-chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla well. Sift in flour, salt and soda. Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 375° in oven.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar.
Continue beating until thick and lemon colored. Add instant pudding mix and vanilla. Beat until mixed. Add Cool Whip, then 2 quarts of milk. You may add more milk if needed to fill freezer.
Pour into freezer and freeze until hard.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix the German chocolate cake mix with melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread (pat) half of the mixture in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes and onions thin.
Mix in salt and cover; let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Make a syrup of the sugar, vinegar, water, turmeric, cloves, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over cukes slices and place over low heat.
Heat but do not boil.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: shipwreck
directions: Seer meat, onion, and celery in heavy skillet until red leaves meat.
Place raw potatoes in bottom of 2 quart casserole dish; put meat mixture over them; next, put drained kidney beans over meat mixture.
Dilute soup with water and pour over all. Season to taste.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain.
Remove from skillet.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Stir in flour; cook and stir 1 minute. Gradually stir in broth and half and half; cook until thickens, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings and cooked sausage.
Serve over hot homemade biscuits.

title: ham medley
directions: Cook vegetables in 1/4 cup margarine until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and cottage cheese.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in ham and noodles.
Transfer to a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots in water to cover in a large saucepan over medium-high heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until very tender.
Drain well.

title: party meatballs
directions: In a crock-pot, combine chili sauce and grape jelly.
Then add meatballs.
Cook until meatballs are done.

title: pineapple and cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to measure 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat liquid; pour over Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Chill until mixture jells.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, nuts, cherries and mayonnaise.
Pour into mold and let set.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Come in!
But don't expect to find

title: mixed hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties.
Fry until done, then pour can of mushroom soup and milk equal to can over top of hamburgers.
Put lid over top and simmer for 10 minutes or so.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and cook 2 minutes until well blended.
This sauce is excellent for brisket, chicken, etc.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to mix well.

title: applesauce cake (ma mc's)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add applesauce and dry ingredients. Then add nuts (floured) and raisins (floured). Add preserves last. Fold in evenly. Bake 1 hour or little more at 350°. This is a moist cake so please don't burn!

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix with melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 10-inch round cake pans.
Mix instant vanilla pudding with milk and combine with ice cream.
Spread over crumb crust.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed candy bars. Refrigerate 12 to 14 hours.
Freezes well.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan; stir continually.
Let come to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate. Melt, then stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Put in buttered pan and let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add raisins and pecans.
Make a well in center.
In separate bowl, lightly beat eggs and egg white or egg replacer. Stir in vanilla, milk and applesauce.
Fold in zucchini.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat all together good.
Put into loaf pan; cover with 3 strips bacon.
Pour over this with 18 ounce Hunt's tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Keep this basted good with sauce.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, then eggs, one at a time.
Add shortening; mix well.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Mix dressing, Miracle Whip and seasonings in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate bark candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover with crackers, placing edge to edge.
Boil butter and sugar together for 3 minutes, stir in vanilla and pour over crackers.
Place in 375° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle chips over top.
Let stand until chips melt, then spread as evenly as possible over the crackers.
Place in freezer overnight. Remove from cookie sheet.
Strip off foil and break into pieces.

title: banana devil's food cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients. Cream shortening, brown sugar and buttermilk. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in bananas. Melt and add the chocolate. Combine buttermilk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Beat well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yields 3 (8-inch) pans. Ice with favorite frosting.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Bake in 3 layers.

title: oatmeal brownie drops
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
In large bowl, beat together sugar and butter until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla, blend thoroughly.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, and baking soda; add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop by Tbsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 7-8 min. till cookies begin to set, do not overbake.

title: chicken and green bean dinner
directions: You will need one Reynolds oven bag, large size (14 x 20-inch).

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Gently remove the 10 outer leaves of cabbage.
Reserve the remaining cabbage for other recipes.
Put 1 inch of water in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; add cabbage leaves.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain cabbage leaves.
Combine beef, onion, rice, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place equal portions in center of cabbage leaves.
Roll up.
Place rolls, seam side down. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Pour tomatoes over and simmer for 1 hour.

title: sausage corn bake
directions: Grease muffin pans.
Heat in a 450° oven.
Combine milk and shortening with egg; mix lightly.
Stir in cornmeal, baking powder, salt, sugar and sausage; blend well.
Pour batter into hot greased pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with scrambled eggs or syrup.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine everything except corn chips and cheese.
Simmer for an hour.
Top each bowl with grated cheese and Fritos corn chips. Serves 10.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Toss all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Top the casserole with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: asparagus and peas
directions: Drain asparagus and peas, reserving liquid.
Cut asparagus into 1-inch pieces.
Arrange half the vegetables in a 3-quart casserole. Place 2 sliced eggs on top.
Pour half the Cheese Sauce over eggs. Repeat layers.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs or bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: crisp potatoes
directions: Mix dry soup mix, margarine and pepper together.
Add potatoes and stir.
Pour potatoes with mixture onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: french dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: watercress rice
directions: Put water and rice in 1 qt. saucepan and cook over high heat until boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed. Stir in watercress and serve.

title: four layer chocolate dessert
directions: Layer, one at a time.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook and take skins off of beets and pack into hot jars. Bring brown sugar, water, and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over beets and seal jars.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together butter or shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly.
Stir in M&M's semi-sweet chocolate candies and nuts.

title: texas snow
directions: Juice grapefruit to make 1 1/2 cups fresh juice.
Combine juice and sugar in saucepan; bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add wine and lemon juice.
Cool.
Freeze to firm.
Stir 1 to 2 times during freezing.

title: rotel dip
directions: Cut cheese up into 1-inch squares.
Cook meat in pan and drain off grease.
Combine ingredients and cook for about 30 minutes on low to melt cheese.
Stir often.

title: magic carrots
directions: Drain carrots.
Melt butter in a saucepan; add sugar, rum or rum flavoring and carrots.
Simmer until sauce just begins to thicken and carrots are glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Sift soda and baking powder with flour.
Add flour and buttermilk, alternating, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla; don't overbeat. Divide batter into two parts.
Make 2 layers that are white. Into other part, add the cinnamon, allspice, cloves and raisins, chopped fine.
Lightly flour raisins.
Make 2 spice layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Combine juice with cornstarch, vinegar, brown sugar and pepper.
Spray pan; saut bell pepper and onion until tender crisp. Remove vegetables and cook chicken.
Stir in vinegar mixture. Cook 2 to 3 minutes until sauce is thick. Add vegetables and pineapple; heat and serve over rice.

title: holiday truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in orange liqueur and frosting; blend well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm. Place coconut in pie pan.
Scoop mixture into 1-inch balls; drop onto coconut.
(Mixture will be sticky.)
Roll to coat.
Place in foil candy cups, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Truffles can also be coated with chocolate sprinkles, ground nuts or cocoa.

title: cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and Miracle Whip until light and fluffy; add cucumber and onions.
Let stand a few hours to blend flavors. Serve on black or rye bread.

title: pork chop marinade
directions: Mix together, pour over chops and refrigerate overnight.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Pour into well-oiled pans (I use clean coffee cans).
Bake or steam at 350° for 2 hours.
Top with lemon sauce.

title: chicken spinach struedel
directions: Filling:
Chop and brown onions.
Add thawed spinach, cheese, chicken, egg, salt and pepper.

title: miriam's noodle goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Stew on low heat on top of stove, approximately 1/2 hour. Add cheese and heat until melted.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 30 min. Do not drain any vegetable.

title: fifth avenue candy bar cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise. Place in 9x13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 candy bar crumbs on top of Twinkies. Mix pudding as directed on box. Pour pudding over mixture. Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding. Sprinkle the rest of the candy bar on top. Refrigerate, if desired.

title: chicken and dumpling soup
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender.
Add cooked chicken.
When mixture boils, add dumpling batter which has been made from Jiffy mix.
Follow recipe on box for dumplings.
Drop by teaspoon into soup.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well, then add cold water. Mix again and add salad dressing. Mix again. Pour batter into 2 well-greased layer cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine morsels, oleo and corn syrup; stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Mix until coated.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill well; cut into squares.

title: creamy broccoli soup with cheese
directions: If frozen broccoli is used, thaw broccoli in colander under hot tap water about 30 seconds.
In larger saucepan, cook and stir onion in butter, about 2 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add broth, whipping cream and broccoli.
Heat and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook and stir (1 minute if using frozen broccoli or 5 to 6 minutes for fresh broccoli), until tender.
Add cheese, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir occasionally.

title: hot tuna burgers
directions: Drain tuna and flake with fork.
Add other ingredients and blend.
Spread on 8 rolls and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In mixing bowl cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla flavoring.
Stir in flour, chopped candied cherries and chopped pecans.
Form dough into two 8-inch rolls.
Roll in flaked coconut to coat outside.
Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap.
Chill thoroughly.

title: chalk
directions: Mix water and plaster in paper cup (add a few drops food coloring if you like).
Pour mixture into a small plastic bag. Roll down top edge of bag, molding mixture into tube shape.
Clip closed bag to a clothesline or hanger.
Wait a day for the plaster to harden.
Unwrap and let dry another day or so before using.

title: raspberry salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine pudding mix, gelatin and water. Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Cool Well. Stir in the raspberries.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken, celery and onion until tender.
Drain.
Chop chicken.
Add grapes, almonds, mayo (amount to your taste) and pepper.
Serve on bread or lettuce.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pan with muffin liner or spray muffin pan with food release.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add mashed banana, eggs, water and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Pour into baking muffin pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 large or 18 medium size muffins.

title: mexi-cheese salad
directions: Combine beans, rice, tomato, bell pepper, cilantro and green onions.
Drop jalapeno pepper in.
Process until minced.
Add oil, lemon juice and cumin.
Blend well.
Toss dressing with bean mixture.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Generously grease sides and bottom of cast-iron skillet or 9-inch square pan. Mix all ingredients and pour into pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy bean salad
directions: Cook green beans according to package directions, drain liquid.
Drain kidney beans and combine with green beans, garlic and red onion.
Blend olive oil and balsamic vinegar well and pour over bean mixture.
Toss well and serve chilled.

title: bacon biscuit cups
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients at medium speed until blended. Stir in cheese and chopped onion. Separate biscuits into 10 portions. Pat each biscuit into a 5-inch circle and press into greased muffin cups, forming a 1/4 inch edge. Sprinkle with half of bacon, and spoon cream cheese mixture evenly on top. Bake at 375° for 22 minutes or until set. Sprinkle with remaining bacon, lightly pressing into filling. Remove from pan and serve warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients the night before serving and refrigerate.

title: taco pie
directions: Partially bake pie crust 10 minutes. Cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and almonds in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until it begins to bubble.
Then sprinkle onion rings on top.
Return to oven about 2 minutes. Serve hot.

title: cheese croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With 2 1/2 to 3-inch scalloped cookie cutter, cut rounds from bread slices.
Reserve crusts for another use.
Place bread rounds on baking sheet.

title: pork and gravy
directions: Cut the pork into serving size pieces.
Season lightly with salt and pepper, dip into flour.
Shake off the excess.
Brown pork in oil in a heavy skillet, removing the meat as it cooks. After all the pork is done, return all meat to skillet and add the water.
Cook, covered, over low heat, 30 minutes.
Remove meat. Dissolve 3 tablespoons flour in the milk.
Bring the liquid in the skillet to a boil and add milk mixture.
Cook, stirring, until gravy thickens.
Return meat to pan and heat through.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll and cut out with floured biscuit cutter. Melt 1/2 stick of butter in a 9 x 13 pan to dip biscuits in (or you can spray the pan with Pam and spray biscuit tops with Pam butter flavor spray). Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or as brown as you like.

title: pacific northwest chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces in margarine and remove to adequate casserole with skin side down.
Then saute vegetables in margarine along with the thyme.
In bowl combine chicken soup and wine and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Let cheese and butter become room temperature; mix with dry ingredients.
Divide into 4 parts; make into rolls (long) and freeze.
After the rolls are frozen, slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or less.
Store in a tight can.

title: coconut cake and frosting
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut together and cover tightly. Let it set overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, bake cake mix as directed.
Let cool and then cut layers in two pieces (making 4 layers).
Keep 1 to 2 cups of coconut filling to frost with.
Then put the coconut filling in between all 4 layers.
Then frost. Keep in refrigerator.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Combine cocoa and coffee; add butter and vanilla extract.
Beat until smooth; add sugar gradually until of spreading consistency (thickens as it cools).

title: minted pecans
directions: Mix
syrup,
sugar
and
water in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until it reaches the soft ball stage.	Remove from heat
and add flavoring and marshmallows.
Add pecans and stir until well coated.
Pour on waxed paper;
separate while still warm.

title: ham, broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(I use Pam in bottom of the pan.)
Layer ham and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over ham and cheese. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg in large bowl.
Stir in milk, corn and 1 tablespoon oil.
Add and beat in flour, baking powder, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Drop tablespoons of mixture into hot oil (375°).
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serve with syrup if desired.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cup; level with a knife.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt, stirring with a whisk.
Combine butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Beat with a mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Add vanilla and egg white; beat 1 minute.
Stir in flour mixture, dried cherries, chocolate chunks and white chocolate chips.
Drop by level tablespoon 2-inches apart onto baking sheets coated with cooking spray.
Place pans in freezer for 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool on pans 2 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: marshmallow pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook on low heat until thick. Cool.
Mix in pineapple, whipping cream and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: party chicken
directions: Line bottom of buttered baking dish with dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast in slice of bacon; place on top of beef. Cover with mixture of sour cream and soup.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Serves 8.

title: teresa's toffee
directions: Put sugar and butter in electric skillet at lowest setting. When light goes out, turn until light comes on again.
Cook until consistency of peanut butter.
Pour into buttered pan and smear top with chocolate bar.
Grind almonds in blender.
Sprinkle top with almonds.
Break up in pieces.

title: my favorite fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° for glass), 8 x 8-inch pan.
In small pan within a larger pan over simmering water in a double boiler, melt the chocolate.
Then add the butter, 1 piece at a time, stirring until each is incorporated into the chocolate. Remove from heat; mix well and let cool to room temperature.
In the medium bowl of an electric mixer, beat eggs, salt, vanilla extract and almond extract until thick and light in color.
Add sugar while continuing to beat about 8 more minutes or until eggs reach the consistency of soft peaked whipped cream.
Thoroughly blend in chocolate mixture and then fold in flour and nut pieces. Spray or lightly butter pan and pour in batter.
Bake in the center of the oven for 35 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted 1 1/2 inches from the edge comes out clean and the top is dry.
Cool in the pan on a rack at least 6 hours before cutting into 30 bars or 36 squares.
If desired, sprinkle brownies lightly with powdered sugar before serving.

title: chili sauce
directions: Select, wash and prepare vegetables.
Chop and combine all vegetables.
Simmer mixture until it begins to thicken.
Add spices and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Remove spices and can in jars.

title: grandma swinehart's molasses cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 minutes. Very good.

title: apple snacks
directions: Halve the apples; cut out cores and slice.
Spread peanut butter on each slice and serve on platter with glasses of cold milk.

title: low-fat fudge brownie sundae
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with cooking spray.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt with 1/4 cup of the cocoa.
Blend in Mott's applesauce, vanilla and milk.
Spoon batter into pan.
Combine brown sugar, rest of the cocoa (1/4 cup) and hot water.
Stir to blend.
Pour over batter in pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove cake and cool in pan.
Serve with scoop of low-fat frozen yogurt and spoon chocolate sauce that has formed on the bottom over the brownie as a topping.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt chips over hot water (not boiling).
When completely melted, pour over chow mein noodles and nuts.
Stir until completely covered.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Chill to set.
Freezes well.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham crackers over the margarine.
Layer coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and milk on top last.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Cut into squares.
So rich it is almost sinful.

title: champion chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken, set aside.
In saucepan combine soups, water, mushrooms, rice and margarine.
Heat slowly and stir over moderate heat until thoroughly blended.
Remove 1 cup mixture, set aside.
Pour sauce into 9 X 13 baking dish, preferably glass. Place chicken on top.
Pour reserved cup of sauce over chicken. Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 hours.
Don't let rice dry out. Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: green pepper-onion cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Combine sugar, vinegar, black pepper, paprika and salt to shredded cabbage.
Add diced green pepper, onions and mayonnaise.
Toss lightly.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into bowl.
Top with one third of the wafers and banana.
Repeat layer.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: orange zucchini bread
directions: Bake @ 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken vito a la nita
directions: Thinly slice and flour chicken.
Saute in olive oil until edges are white.
Turn pepper and brown other side.
Put into baking dish.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add shredded cheese; as much as you want to put in.
Mix all together and roll in a ball.

title: aunt b's buttermilk chicken
directions: Grease long baking pan.
Dip pieces of chicken in buttermilk. Roll in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix cream of chicken soup, buttermilk and water together; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour or until tender at 350°.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Mix well eggs, milk and seasonings.
Toss cheese with flour; add to milk mixture.
Mix; add vegetables.
Mix and pour in pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate fudge topping
directions: Cook and stir continuously; bring to a boil for 1/2 minute. Delicious warm!

title: california pork chops
directions: Brown and drain pork chops.
Combine water and onion soup. Arrange potatoes in greased baking dish.
Lay pork chops on top. Cover with mushrooms.
Pour soup mixture over casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: vegetable cheese spread
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, then stir in last 4.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cecelia's peanut butter "yummies"
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour, slice up immediately.

title: kidney bean and corn chowder soup
directions: In 5-quart saucepot over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion and garlic 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving about 185 calories, 3 grams fat, 1 mg cholesterol and 575 mg sodium.

title: dressed eggs(we don't say "devil" at our house)
directions: Boil a dozen eggs, more or less.
Shell and slice in halves, remove yolks and discard 1/2 yolks (this cuts cholesterol by 50%). Mash the remaining yolks with fork, add sweet pickle relish, seasoned pepper, chives and mayonnaise.
Add a touch of sugar. Beat this mixture so as to puff with air and you won't miss the extra yolks.
Dress the whites with the yolk mixture and sprinkle with paprika if desired.
(Hide from John until ready to serve. He can sure "scarf" them up.)

title: italian pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat. Drain and remove chops from skillet.
Add tomato soup, water, and next six ingredients to skillet, stirring to combine. Return pork chops to skillet.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat, and simmer 30 minutes or until pork chops are tender.

title: egg substitute
directions: Blend egg whites and add dry milk powder, water and coloring. This amount equals 2 eggs.
Contains 74 calories, 0 mg cholesterol, 0 g fat.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat with electric mixer until very smooth.
Chill overnight and serve with crackers.

title: easy strawberry and cream cake
directions: Mix the cake mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan. Bake.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir butter in hot spaghetti; stir cheese mixture and eggs in spaghetti.
Form spaghetti into crust in buttered pie plate or casserole dish.
Cook burger and the rest of ingredients.
Spread on top of spaghetti.
Put extra cheese on top if desired.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Melt butter; stir in flour and chopped onion.
Cook, stirring often, until onion and flour are slightly browned.
Slowly add half and half and chicken broth while stirring.
Cook over low heat; continue stirring until sauce thickens.
Add seasoning and spinach; mix thoroughly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crumble and press into 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: low-fat chocolate-raspberry sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, whisk together sugar, cocoa and arrowroot or cornstarch.
Gradually whisk in 1/4 cup water and jam.
Bring to simmer over medium heat; whisk constantly.
Remove from the heat and stir in framboise, if using.
Let cool slightly.
(The sauce can be stored, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.) Makes 2/3 cup.
Contains 39 calories and 0 g fat per tablespoon.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan and arrange slices of bread real close together and pour mixture of eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla over bread slices.
Put pats of butter on bread slices; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty tomato-cabbage soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Serve with crusty rye bread.

title: moms sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix the above and put in a unbaked crust. Bake 350 degrees 40 minutes.

title: praline topping for cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle over top of cake.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Chop ham and place in bowl. Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard; stir. Unroll crescent dough and press into 1 large rectangle. Cut into 24 pieces. Place dough pieces in mini muffin pan cups. Use fingers to form a cup. Fill cup and bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield: 24.

title: baked pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sweetener, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add vanilla, milk, rind and egg whites; beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad w.w.
directions: Drain fruit, save juice.
Mix pudding with juice from canned fruit. Mix fruit into pudding mixture, add bananas and fold in Cool Whip.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two 9-inch pie pans (this will make its own crust).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Sprinkle bread crumb mixture on top.
Bake in a nonstick casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wilted greens
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add vinegar and water.
Heat.
Combine greens, onions and seasoning.
Pour hot mixture over greens; toss until wilted.
Sprinkle egg on top.

title: easy apricot jam bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients to a crumb consistency.
Put 2/3 of crumbly mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (which has been sprayed with Pam).
Pat the mixture evenly over bottom of dish. Cover and spread evenly with apricot jam.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind dried apricots and coconut together.
Add nuts and condensed milk.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge(original recipe from cocoa can.)
directions: Cook milk, cocoa, syrup and sugar to soft ball stage.
Add margarine and vanilla. Let cool to lukewarm, then beat until it holds shape.
Add nuts and spread in buttered platter.
May use crunchy peanut butter instead of nuts and margarine.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, then molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with other ingredients. Chill.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: one pot stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add everything, stir and bring to a boil.
Cover tightly.
Reduce heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 12 minutes.
Twist pot to stir while cooking.
Never uncover.
Let set for about 10 minutes.
Serve with garlic salt for extra flavor.
Quick, easy, good and great as a leftover.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling cup of water until tender.
Remove carrots.
Add to water 1 cup of sugar and butter.
Cook on low flame until thickens.
Add carrots and vanilla.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of grated cheese on top with stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: party pink candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook to hard ball stage (252°), stirring occasionally.
Combine beaten egg whites and gelatin. Beat until mixture forms peaks.
(May use any flavor gelatin.) Pour hot syrup in thin stream into egg whites, beating until loses gloss and holds shape.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with rows of chopped pecans or coconut.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and blend.
Pour over melted butter in baking dish.
Spread fruit and juice onto batter.
Sprinkle about 2 tablespoons of sugar on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt brown sugar, marshmallows and butter.
Pour over popcorn and mold into balls.

title: yummy yummy cake
directions: Beat pudding, sour cream and milk together for a few minutes. After baked crust is cooled, break into small pieces.
Place half in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add pudding mixture and sliced bananas to remaining crust and pour into pan.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: honey's strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil, water, sugar, jello, flour and cornstarch. Cook until slightly thick.
Cool, then pour over strawberries. Pour in pie shell.
Cool 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: best no-nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch brownie pan.
Melt butter in microwave or stove and cool.
Mix butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in flour.
Mix in cooled, melted unsweetened chocolate.
Mix all together and pour in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Yum!

title: bourbon and chocolate pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, syrup, salt, bourbon and vanilla. Mix until blended. Spread pecans and chocolate chips in bottom of pie shell. Pour filling into shell. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Cream together the sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and salt to boiled mixture.
Spoon out on waxed paper as soon as possible.
Let cool.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix everything together except the egg whites which are beaten stiff and added last.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° to 370° for 1 hour.

title: brioche(serves 8)
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Put the softened yeast in a large bowl and mix well with sugar, salt, milk, egg yolks and eggs. Add 3 cups of flour and stir in with softened butter.
Turn the dough onto a floured surface and knead well for at least 10 minutes, adding flour as necessary.
The dough should form a glossy ball with no stickiness. Place it in a bowl and allow it to double in bulk at room temperature for about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch it down, return it to the bowl and refrigerate overnight.
The slow rise in the refrigerator creates a very good texture.
Remove the dough and let it warm up to room temperature.
Punch it down and roll it into desired shape.
Let it rise until almost double in bulk and bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, more or less, depending on its shape.

title: hot mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon; heat through.
Top with bacon.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: meringue for pie
directions: Beat together egg whites and water until soft peaks form. Then beat in sugar gradually to meringue consistency.
Add vanilla last.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cut up broccoli and cook until almost tender.
Melt margarine and blend in flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add half and half. Drain broccoli, leaving a small amount of water.
Pour half and half mixture over the broccoli.
Add the Cheez Whiz.
Simmer for 15 minutes and stir occasionally.

title: turkey, chicken or ham casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; mix with next five ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cheese as desired.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and edges start to turn brown.
(For color, add a small jar of pimento and some green pepper.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Grease skillet.
Pour in half of dough and spread cheese on top.
Pour remainder of dough on top of cheese and then add the last of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: french dip roast
directions: Place roast in roasting pan on a piece of heavy aluminum foil large enough to wrap meat in.
Douse roast with Worcestershire sauce; seal meat in foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 4 to 5 hours on middle rack.
Remove from from oven; allow to sit 20 minutes before slicing.
Serve with potatoes and carrots. Leftovers make great sandwiches.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Mix together and stuff shells.
Lay stuffed shells in baking dish.
Pour 2 cups cream of chicken soup mixed with 1 cup water over top of shells.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mac-tuna salad
directions: Cool macaroni.
In salad bowl, combine cooled macaroni, tuna and chopped onion.
In separate bowl, mix together mayonnaise, salt, pepper and water (reserved from tuna).
Mix well and add to macaroni and tuna as dressing.
Garnish as desired.

title: sugar-free jello salad
directions: Place pineapple in boiler on stove top and heat to just a boil.
Add Equal and jello.
Place in Pyrex dish and add buttermilk.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat and cut stove off.

title: zucchini bread
