directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Slice zucchini and grate in blender, a few slices at a time.
Add grated zucchini to egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to bowl and mix well.
Bake 1 hour.

title: tee burgers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan, simmer 5 minutes, stirring.
Combine beef with salt and pepper.
Spread raw meat to edge of toasted buns, brush meat with sauce, top with onion slice and brush with additional sauce.
Broil 6 to 8 inches from heat for 5 to 7 minutes, brushing occasionally with sauce until meat is done as you like it.
Makes 12 open sandwiches.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all these and form into 1-inch balls.
Brown them evenly in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Remove as they brown.
Add 1 cup or more boiling water to pan.
To make more gravy, add more hot water and beef bouillon.
Thicken with flour and water mixture. Return meatballs to gravy and simmer 1/2 hour or longer in covered pan.
Serve with rice.

title: cherry party salad supreme
directions: Dissolve red cherry or raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in pie filling.
Turn into cold water rinsed 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Chill until partially set.
Now dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Very gradually beat in lemon jello.
Stir in pineapple and its juice.
Whip heavy cream or 1/2 envelope of dessert topping mix according to package directions.
Fold into lemon mixture with marshmallows.
Spread on top of cherry layer and sprinkle with nuts.

title: ham and swiss rolls
directions: Melt margarine; combine mustard, sugar, onion flakes and poppy seed.
Heat until bubbly.
Slice rolls in half; pour half of mixture on bottom half of rolls.
Place ham slices and cheese slices on bottom half of rolls.
Put top on rolls.
Pour rest of mixture on top of rolls.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed peach-glaze pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and dice peaches, saving the syrup.
In a bowl, mix the water and butter.
Stir in the stuffing mix, peaches and syrup.
Place the stuffing on top of the pork chops or on the side in a baking dish.
Mix the preserves and mustard and brush over the chops and stuffing.
Bake for sixty minutes.

title: icing(caramel)
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Immediately remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm; thicken with powdered sugar.

title: williamsburg holiday aroma
directions: Place all ingredients into a pan on the stove.
Simmer for a couple hours for an old fashioned aroma.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Cook and drain (squeeze) spinach. Beat 3 eggs.
Mix in both cheeses and pepper.
Stir in spinach. Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Beat last egg.
Spread on top of noodle mixture.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brown island dessert
directions: Combine and place in fridge to cool.

title: creamy swiss potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, toss together 1 cup Swiss cheese, onions and dill; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk and add vanilla.
Roll out thin; cut.
Sprinkle sugar over top and bake at 350° until done.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a pie pan.
Spread chili over it.
Shred Monterey Jack cheese and spread over chili.
Heat until cheese is melted.
(Can be put in microwave if glass dish.) Serve with crackers.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Mix other ingredients and add berries. Mix lightly and bake on grill or in frypan.

title: pudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
(Mixture will be dry.)
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: festive chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together mayonnaise or yogurt with paprika and seasoned salt.
Blend in craisins, celery, bell pepper, onion and nuts.
Add chicken and mix well.
Season with black pepper to taste.
Chill 1 hour.

title: grandma's molasses cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add molasses, beaten egg and applesauce.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins. Bake in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° approximately 40 minutes.
Turn out on cake rack; sprinkle with powdered sugar or glaze with 1 1/2 tablespoons of lemon juice, mixed with 3/4 cup confectioners sugar.

title: chicken and peas casserole
directions: Drain peas and cook liquid down to 1/4 or less. Combine drained peas and soup in a casserole. Add liquid. Rub chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Arrange on top, skin side up.
Tuck 1/4 of the bay leaf under each piece. Cover casserole and bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue to bake for 20 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Double recipe for a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and grated cheese.
Add red pepper and flour. Put in cookie press and make sticks about 2 1/2 or 3-inches long. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: gram's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening and sugars.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to sugar mixture.
Then add oats and nuts.
Chill for at least an hour (better overnight).
Then put walnut-sized pieces on a greased cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a small glass.
Dip it in granulated sugar, then flatten out the little round pieces.
Just keep repeating.
Don't need to re-butter the glass bottom, but do re-sugar each time.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes around 6 dozen small cookies.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and egg. Add vanilla, flour and chips.
Place 1 teaspoon mixture on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Once cool, may sprinkle or roll with powdered sugar.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl and mix with hands.
Shape into a ball.
Garnish with parsley and pecans.

title: three bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be done the day before. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Mix onions, 3 1/2 cups cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: snack roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese with Ranch dressing mix, stir well.
Spread on tortillas, sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Roll up, wrap with Saran Wrap.
Chill a few hours.
Slice and serve.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend sugar, soda, cinnamon and flour.
In a saucepan, add margarine, water, Crisco and cocoa; bring to a boil. Then add vanilla and eggs.
Pour over sugar, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic-dill croutons
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Melt butter or margarine in ovenproof skillet or baking pan.
Add garlic salt and dill weed. Add bread cubes.
Toss to coat.
Place in 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until croutons are quite dry and crisp.

title: crab ball
directions: Break crab into small pieces.
Mix cream cheese and crab by hand.
Make into ball.
Pour sauce over crab ball.
Serve with crackers and enjoy!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Next, add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: american chow mein
directions: Boil, bone and dice the chicken.
Add all of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Bake in thin layers at 350 degrees.
Time will depend on size of layer.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir together yogurt, applesauce, powdered sugar, vanilla and spice.
To serve, spear fruit with toothpick, then dip into yogurt mixture.
Makes 6 (3 tablespoon) servings.

title: easy french chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt chocolate.
Mix with melted butter and milk.
Add eggs and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour little by little.
Mix thoroughly.
Lightly grease, or use nonstick, 10-inch diameter cake pan.
Pour mixture in pan.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: german chocolate icing(delicious and easy to prepare)
directions: Cook milk, sugar and margarine until thick and bubbling. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Mix.
Add chopped pecans.
Yield:
Will cover one 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake or two 9-inch layers.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients together.
Chop in the shortening with two knives until fine, like meal.
Add half the milk, then add more gradually to make a soft dough, continuing to mix with the knives.
Use only enough milk to make the dough smooth enough to be handled, but not wet.
Toss on a board which has been lightly floured.
Pat out to about 1/2-inch thickness. Transfer the biscuits to a lightly greased baking tin and bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add hamburger mixture and all remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook in crock-pot on low all day.

title: lobster dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into glass pie plate or quiche dish.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
In skillet brown chops on both sides, pouring off drippings.

title: polynesian meatballs
directions: Step 1:
Place frozen meatballs and onion in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with casserole lid.

title: main dish popover
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add cream cheese and water, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, flour, salt, and milk; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pie plate and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon in meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Top with tomato.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco seasoning, sauce and beans.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan with sour cream.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare instant pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Cut up bananas in with this mixture. Line the bowl with vanilla wafers and put 1/2 of the pudding mixture on top.
Put another layer of vanilla wafers on and then the remainder of the pudding mixture.
Put another layer of vanilla wafers on top of this and spread remainder of the Cool Whip on top. (Using sugar-free pudding and low calorie Cool Whip will change the flavor.)

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill for 2 hours. Pour some powdered sugar into a bowl. Roll cookies into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave margarine and chocolate in a large bowl on High for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Then stir sugar into melted chocolate mixture.
Mix eggs and vanilla until well-blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread into a greased, 8-inch square pan.

title: hot minty chocolate
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt in a 2-quart bowl.
Blend in water. Microwave 2 minutes to boiling.
Stir well.
Add milk, vanilla and peppermint Schnapps.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on Medium.
Do not boil.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mountain mama mud slide
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, 8 ounces Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Spread over crust. Prepare pudding mixes according to package directions.
Spread chocolate pudding over cheese mixture.
Spread vanilla pudding over chocolate pudding.
Let pudding set for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with additional Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with shavings from a chocolate bar or mini chocolate bits.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Stir often.
Add macaroni and tomatoes.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Stir in vanilla and rhubarb.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Before baking, sprinkle 1/2 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon on top.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with tomato slices; dot with dressing and butter.
Cover with corned beef; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Remove casserole from oven.

title: baked halibut
directions: Place the halibut in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix together mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and onions. Spread mayonnaise mixture over the halibut. Bake at 350° until fish pulls apart easily. Mayonnaise mixture will be a golden brown. (Do not overcook.)

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.
For variety, you may add 1/2 c. chopped nuts.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Fry hamburger.
Drain.
Add onion.
Cook a few minutes.
Add soup, sauce, Milnot and chilies.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Doritos; add hamburger.
Pour sauce over chips and hamburger; add another layer of chips and cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and drain well. Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: italian sauce(good)
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Stir in tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Serve sauce with spaghetti, lasagna or manicotti. Yields 7 1/2 cups.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Debone chicken and combine with beans and 1/2 jar of water. Cook on medium-low until thickened.
Pour over tortilla chips, add taco sauce and sour cream to taste.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Shape into loaf and place in baking pan.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: paella
directions: Brown rice and garlic in oil over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes.
Add 3 cups chicken stock, pimento, oregano, green pepper, black pepper and chorizo.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Add chicken, shrimp, peas and tomatoes.
Bring mixture to boil, cover and cook over very low heat for 15 minutes. Add more stock if necessary.
(Can bake in oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.)

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter or margarine in small mixer bowl; add cocoa and confectioners sugar, alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency; blend in vanilla (about 2 cups frosting).

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix
lemon
juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add Cool Whip, then rest of ingredients.
Mix together and put in pie crusts. Let set awhile in refrigerator.

title: oven barbecued ribs
directions: Salt ribs; place in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up.
Roast at 425° about 30 minutes.
Drain excess fat from pan.
Pour sauce over ribs for 1 hour.
(After the first 30 minutes, reduce heat to 400°.)

title: magic blueberry pie
directions: Add lemon juice to milk.
Fold Dream Whip into lemon mixture. Fold in blueberries.
Pour into crumb crust; chill thoroughly. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: smothered steak and onions
directions: Combine bouillon granules and hot water; stir well, and set aside.
Sprinkle steaks with lemon-herb seasoning.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add steaks; cook 2 minutes in each side or until browned. Add onion and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 12 minutes or until onion is tender.
Remove steaks and onion from skillet with a slotted spoon; set aside. and keep warm. Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water, stir well.
Add to cooking liquid in skillet; cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Place rice on a plate and top with steak and onion.
Divide gravy evenly over each serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix half of cake mix (dry) with
margarine,
brown
sugar,
water and eggs in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and 1 cup nuts. Spread in
pan
and bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top and bake 10 more minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute; remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once; continue beating until smooth.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool; cut off tops and fill with cream filling.
Replace tops; dust with powdered sugar.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken without skin until tender.
Let chicken cool, shred the chicken and put aside.
Lightly fry tortillas in oil. Dip the tortillas in the enchilada sauce; roll with chicken and place in a greased pan.
Pour the remaining sauce over the tortilla rolls.
Garnish with cheese, green onion and olives. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed 'n' tender pork chops
directions: Power Level: Medium.
Microwave Time: 35 to 40 minutes, total.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Alternate slices of potatoes and onions in a buttered casserole, dotting each layer with butter, salt and pepper. Combine the cream of chicken or mushroom soup with milk; mix thoroughly and pour over the vegetables.
Lift the potatoes and onions so that the soup is well mixed with them.
Top all with the sliced cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until the potatoes are tender.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then cut butter in.
In greased casserole or pie plate, place berries, then pack down oatmeal mixture on top of berries.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Allow to cool for a few minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: "grandma strom's fruit nut bread"
directions: Put whole dates, cherries and pecans in a large bowl. In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Pour over fruit mixture, mix well. Then add well-beaten eggs and vanilla. Work with hands. Put in two well greased wax paper lined loaf pans - 2/3 full. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven. Cool before removing from pans. Remove waxed paper immediately after taking bread out of pans. Makes two large loaves. Wrap in waxed paper and then foil. After a few days, if you have not used all, put in refrigerator.
YUMMY!!

title: buttermilk flapjacks
directions: Beat egg.
Add rest ingredients.
Will be slightly lumpy. Cook and serve.

title: homestyle oyster stew
directions: Cut up onion into very small pieces.
Put into a boiler with a small amount of water and boil for about 15 minutes.
Pour water off.
Drain water from oysters and pour into boiler with onions. Add 1/4 stick of margarine.
Add sweet milk, salt and black pepper to season.
Do not bring to a boil, just get real hot and serve with crackers.
Delicious during cold and rainy weather.
Serves 4.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by level tablespoon on a greased or sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Cook spinach (reserve juice, add water to equal 1 cup).
Set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Saut hamburger and onion until lightly browned; drain.
Add spinach juice, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes. Combine spinach, macaroni, cheese and eggs.
Pour mixture into 8 x 13 inch cake pan.
Top with meat sauce and arrange button mushrooms on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: mandarin orange 7-up salad
directions: Topping:
Save juice from pineapple and orange.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 cup chopped nuts; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Punch holes in top of cake as soon as it is removed from the oven and spoon Coconut Icing over cake.

title: meggett spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt, sugar and milk. Heat in double boiler until thick. Cool. Add 1 teaspoon baking powder. Beat egg yolks and whites of eggs separately. Add to cornmeal mixture, the egg yolks and melted butter. Fold in egg whites. Bake for 45 minutes in buttered baking dish at 300°. Serve promptly.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer all the ingredients in the order listed.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine the sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add the vanilla, apples, coconut and nuts.
Stir by hand.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pan. Saute hash browns together with butter (lightly browned). Add chopped onion (do not let onions caramelize; don't overcook). Add soup. Mix well. Bring to a boil. Mix sour cream and cheese. Mix well. Remove from heat. Place in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: tuna burger
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste. Split and butter 6 hamburger buns.
Fill buns with tuna mixture and replace tops.
Heat in paper sandwich bags on baking sheets at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat.
Combine dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with water.
Stir in pumpkin and chopped nuts.
Put batter in 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: company's coming cake
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff.
Add sugar and cream of tartar. Fold crushed crackers into egg whites, then add nuts and vanilla. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool. Top with desired amount of Cool Whip (8 to 16 ounces) and shredded coconut.

title: italian style meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine beef, egg, onion, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Put mixture into a 9-inch pie pan and shape as a crust.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Pour off excess grease.
Meanwhile, prepare pasta according to package.
Drain well.
Spoon pasta into baked meat crust; pour sauce evenly over pasta.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs and cheese over pie and return to oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chile verde
directions: Boil tomatillos and chiles until soft.
Add cilantro and boil 3 to 5 minutes, then blend solids until smooth.
Brown pork roast. Add meat to sauce with garlic and simmer in crock-pot all day. Serve with flour tortillas or as burritos.

title: salmagundies cheese soup(serves 6)
directions: Steam the onion, broccoli, carrots, cauliflower and potatoes until fork can go through!

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of pie crust.
Layer with pineapple. Mix pudding and cream cheese; layer on top of pineapple.
Chill for 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream.
Add nuts and cherries and serve.

title: quick raisin bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together; set aside.
Mix shortening and sugar until smooth.
Stir in egg mix and half of the water until smooth.
Add rest of water.
Beat well.
Mix half of flour mixture and milk into the egg mixture. stir in rest of flour and milk just until smooth.
Stir in raisins.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) about 40 minutes until browned.
Cool bread in pan for 10 minutes.

title: baked potato surprise
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and cube.
Combine all ingredients, except bacon, and put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crumble bacon on top.
Bake for 45 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Great for brunches and dinners.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, sugar, flour and salt in ungreased casserole. Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add milk; mix well.
Dot butter on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Bring to boil, the milk and oleo.
Mix together sugar, cornstarch, well-beaten eggs and nutmeg or vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well and pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Divide equal parts of the batter. Add to one part, 1 tsp. allspice, 1/4 tsp. cinnamon, 1 tsp. nutmeg, and 1 cup raisins. Bake at 325° until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing, and place in casserole. Sprinkle top with dressing sauteed in butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients except chicken in bowl.
Place chicken in metal baking pan.
Pour sauce over.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: clam chip dip
directions: Put in blender and whip until smooth.
Add half can of minced clams (freeze other half for next time).
Mix slightly.
Chill for half hour, if possible.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour sauce over meat loaf.

title: aunt pat's lemon chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/2 inch thickness with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Brown chicken.
Transfer to 9 inch x 13 inch baking dish.
In skillet add sherry, onion, lemon rind, and lemon juice.
Cook until onion is tender.	Add water and bouillon.
Combine 1/4 cup water and flour.
Stir.
Add to liquid in skillet.
Cook and stir until thick.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese, paprika, and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes for approximately 20 minutes or until soft.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry meat
until
brown,
but don't overcook, along with onions, garlic
and
spices.
Add
tomato puree and sauce with equal amounts of
water.
Simmer slowly about 2 hours or until thick and grease forms on the top.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.

title: miniature puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffs are golden brown and dry, about 25 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: asparagus carrot casserole
directions: Make sauce with milk, asparagus juice, margarine, flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Layer carrots, asparagus and sauce in baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix the potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and French dressing together.
Chill an hour or two and toss lightly with mayonnaise. Carefully blend in the eggs.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: spinach squares
directions: Place spinach in a strainer; rinse under hot water to thaw, then press out all water.
Set aside.
Melt butter in frying pan over medium heat; add onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, until onion is limp.
In a bowl, beat eggs with a fork, then stir in bread crumbs, mushroom soup, 2 tablespoons of the cheese, pepper, basil, oregano, spinach and onion until blended.
Turn into a well-greased 9-inch square pan with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 35 minutes, or until set when lightly touched.
Cool slightly, then cover and refrigerate. Serve cold or warm.

title: pork chop-potato scallop
directions: Brown chops. Blend next 4 ingredients. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish, alternating with sliced potatoes. Salt and pepper. Top with chops. Cover. Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain.
Cut the crust off bread and place in buttered casserole dish.
Crumble cooked sausage over bread slices.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and pour in milk.
Add salt.
Pour over bread, sausage and cheese.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Take out next morning, remove wrap and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine chicken, chicken stock, carrots, celery, onion and oregano.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Lower the heat to medium and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove the chicken from the pan and set aside for 5 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
Cut into bite size pieces.
While the chicken is cooling, stir the noodles into the stock.
Cook for 8 minutes or until just tender.
Stir in the parsley and chicken.
Serves 6.
Contains 186 calories per serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add pineapple with juice and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt and add to sugar mixture. Beat well. Stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In a saucepan, melt oleo.
Add brown sugar; boil over low heat, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Add milk; stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; cool.
Slowly add powdered sugar.
Beat after each addition until thick.
Pour over hot cake.

title: barley (tabbouleh) salad
directions: Toss cooked barley in a large bowl with the olive oil, lemon juice and garlic.
Add the chopped mint and dill.
Toss in tomatoes, cucumbers and scallions.
Season with salt and pepper. Toss gently, but thoroughly.
Let rest for 1 hour so the flavors can blend.
Garnish with sprigs of mint or dill before serving. Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients to form crust in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix hamburger, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, sugar, oregano and garlic powder and simmer.
Put 1 cup cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Spread on hamburger mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in heated juices from cherries and pineapple. Add Coke, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Congeal.

title: hot seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain.
Add Sea Stix, broccoli and spices and toss with melted butter or margarine.
May be heated in microwave for 3 minutes on High before serving.

title: 100 year old black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening.
Add sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extracts to milk.
Add baking powder to flour.
Alternately add liquid and dry ingredients to batter.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until cake is tested done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In
long pan put the cooked chicken, vegetables and the potatoes.
Pour
chicken
gravy
over all of this.	Add 2 teaspoons
onion salt.
Make biscuits.
Cut shortening into flour until
it
becomes	coarse crumbs. Add milk all at once.
Stir quickly until dough follows form around bowl.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead gently; roll out and cut out biscuits. Add biscuits
to
top of mixture. Bake at 350° until biscuits are done, about 40 or 45 minutes.

title: squash cakes
directions: Place squash and onion in blender with enough water to cover. Process until finely chopped.
Drain.
Add flour, salt, pepper and egg.
Mix well.
Form into croquettes.
Fry in hot oil.
When brown on bottom, turn over and press flat while browning other side.

title: walnut glory cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon and salt.
Beat egg whites in a large mixing bowl until soft mounds form.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar. Continue beating together until very stiff.
Do not underbeat.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavorings, beating after each.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie and crust
directions: Stir together sweet potatoes, cinnamon, honey and chopped pecans.
Then add rest of ingredients and mix together with a hand mixer very well.
Add this mixture to unbaked pie shell (recipe follows).
Bake for 60 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor and chill. Serve with fresh vegetables, chips, crackers or bread.
Keeps well.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat in margarine. Mix all other ingredients; stir in meat.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: In medium bowl, mix spinach, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, nutmeg and pepper; set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and caraway seed alternately with sour milk and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: roast and golden gravy
directions: Put roast in big stainless steel pot.
Put all ingredients on roast.
Cover roast with 1 1/2 inches of water over ingredients. Cook at 150° to 200° overnight.
Put mushroom soup in.
Let cook for about 4 hours.
Good for Sunday dinner after church.
Good over rice.
Stir soup in with roast.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix together and let stand 1/2 hour.
Push by teaspoons on greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cake will stick.
Grease 10-inch tube pan thickly with shortening.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy, then add oil, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Coat dates with 3 tablespoons of flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Mix with mixer the eggs and sugar only. Use heavy wooden spoon.
Batter is very stiff.)
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: crab and shell salad
directions: Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Place cooked lima beans in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions in large skillet. Saute chicken, mushrooms and onions until chicken is cooked through and vegetables are tender.
(A small amount of butter can be used to saute.)
In casserole dish, mix together rice, chicken mixture and soup.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix together apples, 2 packets Sweet 'N Low, cinnamon, raisins and water.
Place in pie plate and microwave 4 minutes.
Mix margarine, 1 packet Sweet 'N Low, walnuts, baking powder and nutmeg.
Sprinkle this on top of apple mixture and place in oven to bake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse dry green split peas.
In a pot combine peas, cold water, beef bouillon, onion, bay leaf, pepper and marjoram.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in carrots and celery.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes more.
Season.

title: royal batter bread
directions: Grease coffee cans and lids, or spray well with Pam.
Dissolve yeast in water in large mixing bowl.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and salt, stirring well.
Add milk and oil and stir well.
Slowly add flour, mixing well.
Dough will be thick and gooey.
Spoon batter evenly into the two prepared coffee cans and lightly set lids on top.
DO NOT SEAL THE LIDS!! Let rise until the lids fall off.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: Saute the onion, carrot and celery lightly but not brown. Stir in the flour and curry powder.
Stir and cook for 3 minutes. Add chicken broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Add apple, rice, chicken and pepper.
Simmer for another 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put ingredients, except corn flakes, in pan.
Cover crushed corn flakes over top.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Take foil off and bake 30 more minutes.

title: homemade corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; stir until smooth.
Pour ingredients in a greased hot, deep skillet.
Sprinkle a little portion of corn meal in skillet to keep from sticking.
Cook at 375° for 30 or 35 minutes, then take out or leave in skillet and cut into slices after it has cooled off.

title: grape jam
directions: Separate pulp from skins of grapes. If desired, chop skins in a food blender or chopper.

Cook skins gently 15 to 20 minutes, adding only enough water to prevent sticking (about 1/2 cup). Cook pulp without water until soft; press through a sieve of food mill to remove seeds. Combine pulp, skins and sugar. Bring slowly to boiling, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves. Cook rapidly almost to jellying point, about 10 minutes. As mixture thickens, stir frequently to prevent sticking. Pour, boiling hot, into sterilized Ball jars. Adjust caps. Yield: About 3 pints.

title: chip dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Simmer.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: butter steak sauce
directions: Put butter in a small bowl; let soften.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add lemon juice, pepper, chopped parsley, dried tarragon and Tabasco sauce.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate. Makes 1 cup.

title: breast of chicken sauté maison(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 425°.

title: beef and cheese turnovers
directions: Make pastry as usual.
Roll out to make 8 (5-inch) circles.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Brown onion and garlic in butter with pepper. Mix potato soup, cream cheese, half and half, corn and shrimp. Simmer, don't boil, about 10 minutes. (Note: Use little salad shrimp (frozen) or I like the bigger, medium size.)

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, shortening and buttermilk. Mix all together.
Fill muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Store remaining batter in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add sugar, salt and half of the flour.
Beat with spoon, then add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of the flour.
Let rise until double, about 30 minutes. Stir down raised dough. Spoon into muffin cups.
Let rise again 20 to 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 rolls.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Chop peppers, zucchini and onion.
Saute in olive oil. Combine in stockpot the kidney beans, tomatoes and puree.
Add cooked peppers, zucchini and onion.
Mince garlic cloves.
Add chili powder, garlic and oregano.
Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve topped with Cheddar cheese.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: skillet cake
directions: Sift into ungreased iron skillet the flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
In first hole, add oil.
In 2nd hole, add vinegar.
In 3rd hole, add vanilla. Pour cold water over all.
Stir well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Frost while warm.

title: peach or apricot brandy
directions: Mix ingredients together and let sit for at least 4 weeks.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar, water and salt until clear (medium heat).
Take off heat and add 4 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Let cool until thick (not congealed) before adding sliced strawberries.
Put small amount of thickened mixture over bottom of cooked crust before adding mixture of strawberries.
Serve with a drop of Cool Whip on top.
Wonderful!

title: seafood impossible pie
directions: In blender, mix together Bisquick, milk, egg and Mrs. Dash. Arrange fish and seafood in buttered casserole.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° for 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mrs. thomlinson's scones
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Add margarine and cut in.
Add raisins.
Separate the egg yolk from one egg.
Set aside.
Beat remaining egg white and whole egg with milk.
Combine mixtures and mix with a few strokes.
Turn out on a floured board and pat 3/4-inch thick.
Cut in triangles and place on a greased pan.
Brush top with egg yolk; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Boil mushrooms and celery in water to cover for 3/4 of an hour.
Melt butter; blend in milk, cream and flour.
Heat and season to suit taste.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Combine the 2 teaspoons soy sauce, 1 teaspoon cornstarch and pepper.
Add chicken, tossing to coat.
Let stand 20 minutes (longer in refrigerator).
Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in wok over high heat.
Stir-fry chicken 2 or 3 minutes or until white.
Push up sides of wok.
Add remaining oil.
Stir-fry onion 1 minute.
Add pea pods.
Stir-fry until tender-crisp, then mix with chicken. Combine remaining soy sauce, cornstarch and chicken broth.
Add to wok, cooking until thickened.
Stir in cashews.
Garnish with green onion.
Serve with hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine well.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet and top with pecan halves.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
